   @{"PFM (PNM HDR)"          LINK SVOBJECT_PFM }           EXT   24/48bit files         24/48bit files
   @{"PNG (Network Gfx)"      LINK SVOBJECT_PNG }       EXT   max 8/24/48bit files   max 8/24/48bit files
   @{"PAM (*nix)"             LINK SVOBJECT_PAM }              EXT   max 8/24/48bit files   max 8/24/48bit files
   @{"PNM (*nix)"             LINK SVOBJECT_PNM }              EXT   max 8/24/48bit files   max 8/24/48bit files
   @{"Postscript/PDF"         LINK SVOBJECT_GhostScript } *        EXT   -> @{fg highlight}Ghostscript@{fg text}         (not available)
   @{"PSD (Ph*t*sh*p)"        LINK SVOBJECT_PSD }         EXT   1/8/24bit files        8/24bit files
   @{"PSP (PaintSh*pPr*)"     LINK SVOBJECT_PSP }      EXT   1/4/8/24bit files      (not available)
   @{"PXR (P*xar)"            LINK SVOBJECT_PXR }             EXT   max 24bit files      (not available)
   @{"QRT/POV"                LINK SVOBJECT_QRT }                 EXT   24bit files            24bit files
   @{"RAW (SView-Library)"    LINK SVOBJECT_RAW }     EXT   (not available)        8/24/48bit files (only raw pixels)
   @{"RAW-ALPHA"              LINK SVOBJECT_RAW-ALPHA }               EXT   (not available)        only alpha data (8 bit for 24/48 bit)
   @{"RAW-CM (SView-Library)" LINK SVOBJECT_RAW-CM }  EXT   (not available)        8bit files (only raw colormaps)
   @{"RAW-META"               LINK SVOBJECT_RAW-META }                EXT   (not available)        only meta data (EXIF, IPTC, XMP0, XMP1)
   @{"Scitex SCT/CT"          LINK SVOBJECT_CT }                     EXT   max 8/24bit files      (not available)
   @{"SGI"                    LINK SVOBJECT_SGI }                     EXT   max 8/24bit files      only 24bit files
   @{"Sinclair QL"            LINK SVOBJECT_QL }             EXT   max 4bit files         (not available)
   @{"Spectrum SCR/TAP"       LINK SVOBJECT_Spectrum }        EXT   max 4bit files         (not available)
   @{"SPP"                    LINK SVOBJECT_SPP } *                   EXT   -> @{fg highlight}SPP@{fg text}                 (24 Bit via SPP)
   @{"SunRaster (RAS)"        LINK SVOBJECT_RAS }         EXT   max 8/24bit files      max 8/24bit files
   @{"SGX (SView Gfx)"        LINK SVOBJECT_SVG } *       EXT   max 8/24/48bit files   max 8/24/48bit files
   @{"SVG (W3C)"              LINK SVOBJECT_SVGW3C } *             EXT   -> @{fg highlight}svg2png@{fg text}             -> @{fg highlight}potrace@{fg text}
   @{"Targa"                  LINK SVOBJECT_TARGA }                   EXT   max 8/24bit files      max 8/24bit files
   @{"TIFF"                   LINK SVOBJECT_TIFF }      EXT   max 8/24/48bit files   max 8/24/48bit files
   @{"TIM"                    LINK SVOBJECT_TIM }                     EXT   max 8/24bit files      (not yet available)
   @{"Utah RLE"               LINK SVOBJECT_UtahRLE }                EXT   24bit files            24bit files
   @{"WBMP (WAP BM)"          LINK SVOBJECT_WBMP }          EXT   max 1bit files         max 1bit files
   @{"WMF"                    LINK SVOBJECT_MetaView } *                   EXT   -> @{fg highlight}MetaView 1.x@{fg text}        (not available)
   @{"WPG (WP-Draw BitMap)"   LINK SVOBJECT_WPG }    EXT   max 8bit files         max 8bit files
   @{"WPG (WP-Draw Drawing)"  LINK SVOBJECT_MetaView } * EXT   -> @{fg highlight}MetaView 2.x@{fg text}        (not available)
   @{"XBM"                    LINK SVOBJECT_XBM }                     EXT   max 1bit files         max 1bit files
   @{"XPM"                    LINK SVOBJECT_XPM }                     EXT   max 8bit files         max 8 bit files
   @{"XWD"                    LINK SVOBJECT_XWD }                     EXT   max 8/24bit files      (not available)

   @{"DataTypes"              LINK SVOBJECT_DATATYPES }               INT   all Picture DTs        (not available)

    @{fg highlight}* SV5Objects marked with an Asterisk will only work, when               @{fg text}
    @{fg highlight}  the mentioned external programs (usually freely distributable        @{fg text}
    @{fg highlight}  software from AmiNet) also have been installed and set up as needed. @{fg text}
      (If not set up, these may be disabled via controlpad STATUS=DISABLED.)

  There's also an @{"Unpack.sv5object" LINK SVOBJECT_UNPACK }, which allows reading of
  packed files without explicitely unpacking these before (supports XPK and PP20 directly
  and GZ/BZ2 if gzip/bzip2 is somewhere in the search path).

  It also supports reading of Mac-written HQX files directly (BinHex compression)
  without having to extract the data fork before.

  It is as well possible to save graphics as @{"C or Asm-Sourcecode" LINK SVOBJECT_CSource }.


  Planned SV5Objects (no guarantee !) :

     - Rendition
     - various raw formats
     - more Atari formats
        (if I get my hands on some pictures -> @{"send" LINK CORRESPONDENCE } some, if PD !)
     - and more
        (you may @{"send" LINK CORRESPONDENCE } me gfx's and/or descriptions, if PD)

    Please ask before sending graphics via email.

@ENDNODE

