@NODE SVOPERATORS "Overview of currently available SV5Operators"

  Available SV5Operators (mostly included) :

   SV5Operator

   @{"24BitToHAM" LINK SVOPERATOR_24BitToHAM }          dithers 24 bit RGB to HAM6/HAM8
   @{"AddAlpha" LINK SVOPERATOR_AddAlpha }            adds an alpha channel to a 24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"AddText" LINK SVOPERATOR_AddText }             renders text into a 8/24 bit graphics (*)
   @{"AddTransColor" LINK SVOPERATOR_AddTransColor }       adds a transparent color to a 8 bit graphics (*)
   @{"AlphaBlend" LINK SVOPERATOR_AlphaBlend }          blends two (three) 24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Antique" LINK SVOPERATOR_Antique }             creates a nice "antique" look from 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"AnyTo24Bit" LINK SVOPERATOR_AnyTo24Bit }          converts input to 24 bit
   @{"AnyTo48Bit" LINK SVOPERATOR_AnyTo48Bit }          converts input to 48 bit
   @{"AutoBorder" LINK SVOPERATOR_AutoBorder }          removes single-colored border frames from 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Blur" LINK SVOPERATOR_Blur }                applies blur filter to 24/48bit graphics
   @{"Brightness" LINK SVOPERATOR_Brightness }          adjusts brightness of an 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"CallPNM" LINK SVOPERATOR_CallPNM }             call preset external PNM operator (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"ChangePalette" LINK SVOPERATOR_ChangePalette }       change palette of graphics
   @{"ChangeColor" LINK SVOPERATOR_ChangeColor }         exchange palette (colormap) entry with RGB value
   @{"ChangePixel24" LINK SVOPERATOR_ChangePixel24 }       exchange pixel RGB value with different RGB value
   @{"ColorCycle" LINK SVOPERATOR_ColorCycle }          rotates RGB components of 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Complement" LINK SVOPERATOR_Complement }          creates the complement of an 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"Contrast" LINK SVOPERATOR_Contrast }            adjusts contrast of an 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"Convolve" LINK SVOPERATOR_Convolve }            applies a 3x3 convolution matrix to 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"ConvolveFloat" LINK SVOPERATOR_ConvolveFloat }       applies a 3x3 convolution (floating point) matrix to 8/24 bit image (*)
   @{"ConvolveNxN" LINK SVOPERATOR_ConvolveNxN }         applies a 5x5/7x7 or 9x9 convolution matrix to 8/24 bit image (*)
   @{"Crop" LINK SVOPERATOR_Crop }                "crops" boxes of any size from 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"Cut" LINK SVOPERATOR_Cut }                 "cuts" holes of any size into 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"CutInverse" LINK SVOPERATOR_CutInverse }          "cuts" part of any size from 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Dither24Bit" LINK SVOPERATOR_Dither24Bit }         dithers 24 bit RGB to 2..256 colors
   @{"DitherFix24" LINK SVOPERATOR_DitherFix24 }         dithers 24 bit RGB to 2..256 colors using fixed palette
   @{"EdgeDetect" LINK SVOPERATOR_EdgeDetect }          applies an edge detection algorithm to 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"ExtractAlpha" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractAlpha }        extracts alpha channel from image (*)
   @{"ExtractBlue" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractBlue }         extracts blue values from 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"ExtractChannel" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractChannel }      extracts red/green/blue 8/16 bit channel from 24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"ExtractGrayScales" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractGrayScales }   converts (upto) 256 colors or 24/48 bit to grayscales
   @{"ExtractGreen" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractGreen }        extracts green values from 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"ExtractRed" LINK SVOPERATOR_ExtractRed }          extracts red values from 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"FixAlphaBlend" LINK SVOPERATOR_FixAlphaBlend }       blends 24/48 bit graphics using fix alpha / source alpha (*)
   @{"FlipNibbles" LINK SVOPERATOR_FlipNibbles }         operates on the nibbles/bytes of pixel values/components (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"Gamma" LINK SVOPERATOR_Gamma }               adjusts gamma of an 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"Ghost" LINK SVOPERATOR_Ghost }               applies a ghosting effect to a 24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"HilbertDither256" LINK SVOPERATOR_HilbertDither256 }    dithers to Black & White
   @{"Histogram" LINK SVOPERATOR_Histogram }           calculates RGB color occurance in a 24/48 bit image
   @{"InvertAlpha" LINK SVOPERATOR_InvertAlpha }         inverts existing alpha channel/map of image (optinally adds one) (*)
   @{"InvertColors256" LINK SVOPERATOR_InvertColors256 }     inverts a colormapped image's palette
   @{"LeftToRight" LINK SVOPERATOR_LeftToRight }         flips left and right of 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"Mirror" LINK SVOPERATOR_Mirror }              mirrors an 8/24/48 bit image by point or axis (*)
   @{"Mosaic" LINK SVOPERATOR_Mosaic }              applies mosaic effect to 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Move" LINK SVOPERATOR_Move }                "cuts" area of any size from 8/24/48 bit graphics and moves it by some pixels (*)
   @{"NegateColors" LINK SVOPERATOR_NegateColors }        turns a 8/24 bit image into its complement
   @{"OptimizePalette" LINK SVOPERATOR_OptimizePalette }     reduces depth by filtering unused or redundant colors
   @{"PagePrint" LINK SVOPERATOR_PagePrint }           creates a thumbail overview page from various images
   @{"PaletteDither" LINK SVOPERATOR_PaletteDither }       dithers (optionally in parts) to a user-supplied palette
   @{"ReplaceBorder" LINK SVOPERATOR_ReplaceBorder }       replaces single-colored border frames around 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Resize" LINK SVOPERATOR_Resize }              resizes to given new width and height; 8/24/48 bit images
   @{"ResetChannel" LINK SVOPERATOR_ResetChannel }        resets red/green/blue 8/16 bit channel of 24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"RGBAdjust" LINK SVOPERATOR_RGBAdjust }           separately adjusts RGB values of 8/24/48 bit image (*)
   @{"Rotate" LINK SVOPERATOR_Rotate }              rotates by 90/180/270 degrees (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"RotateFree" LINK SVOPERATOR_RotateFree }          rotates freely by 0..360 degrees about a given point (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"Scale50" LINK SVOPERATOR_Scale50 }             scales to half/double size (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"ScaleDDA" LINK SVOPERATOR_ScaleDDA }            scales by given zoom factor (8/24/48 bit)
   @{"ScaleFree" LINK SVOPERATOR_ScaleFree }           (much like Resize - supports 8/24/48 bit graphics) (*)
   @{"Scatter" LINK SVOPERATOR_Scatter }             applies scatter effect to 8/24/48 bit graphics (*)
   @{"Sharpen" LINK SVOPERATOR_Sharpen }             applies sharpen operator to 24/48 bit graphics
   @{"StripAlpha" LINK SVOPERATOR_StripAlpha }          removes existing alpha channel/map or transparent color from image (*)
   @{"TopToBottom" LINK SVOPERATOR_TopToBottom }         flips top and bottom of 8/24/48 bit graphics
   @{"XOR" LINK SVOPERATOR_XOR }                 applies an XOR operation to 8 bit graphics

   @{fg highlight}(*) SV5Operators marked with an Asterisk yet lack a detailed documentation (sorry!) @{fg text}

     Just for information:

      - this distribution also includes a bunch of image processing
        operators by Steve Quartly (SQOperators) like:

         SQBentley.sv5operator             SQBlur.sv5operator
         SQContrast.sv5operator            SQDeep_Press.sv5operator
         SQDiffuse.sv5operator             SQEmboss.sv5operator
         SQHighPass.sv5operator            SQMosaic.sv5operator
         SQMotion_Blur.sv5operator         SQOilPaint.sv5operator
         SQSharpen.sv5operator             SQSlicing.sv5operator
         SQThreshold.sv5operator           SQTiling.sv5operator

         Descriptions can be found @{"here" LINK SQOPERATORS }

      - planned SV5Operators (no guarantee !) :

         - some more operators for common image processing
         - and more

@ENDNODE

@NODE SQOPERATORS "SQOperator List"

  SQBentley:
    This module takes a graphics buffer and then applies an effect that makes
    the image look ghostly (24 bit only).

  SQBlur:
    This module takes a graphics buffer and then applies an effect that blurs
    the image (24 bit only).

  SQContrast:
    This operator allow you to adjust the contrast of an image (24 bit only).

  SQDeep_Press:
    This operator creates a chiseled effect in the image (24 bit only).

  SQDiffuse:
    This  operator  creates  an  effect as if the image was exploded pixel by
    pixel (24 bit only).
    A  PERCENTAGE=10  control pad setting gives a very nice effect, the image
    is  still  recognizable.  While a PERCENTAGE=100 is just a mess.... but a
    nice one!

  SQEmboss:
    This operator embosses the image (24 bit only).
    Applying the ExtractGrayScales.svoperator after the SQEmboss.svoperator
    will enhance the effect.

  SQHighPass:
    This  operator  applies  a  high  pass  filter  to  the  image  giving an
    interesting "painted coloured" effect (24 bit only).
    It  can  give  some  really wierd effects, try setting the control pad to
    PERCENTAGE=10  for  a  negative  type effect, or PERCENTAGE=99 for a real
    colourful effect!

  SQMosaic:
    This operator applies a square block mosaic to the image (24 bit only).

  SQMotion_Blur:
    This  operator is another kind of blur, however this one looks a bit like
    a motion blur (24 bit only).

  SQOilPaint:
    This operator applies an oil paint effect to an image (24 bit only).
    This  effect  takes  a  quite  long  time to apply as the effect is quite
    complex. The larger the range, the longer it takes to apply.

  SQSharpen:
    This operator sharpens an image (24 bit only).

  SQSlicing:
    This operator slices up an image into horizontal and
    vertical strips (24 bit only).
    Although  you  have  the  option  to  be  able  to  limit  the slice to a
    recangular  region, the routine produces unpredictable results on smaller
    regions. If you maintain a larger area, you will get much better results.

  SQThreshold:
    This operator converts an image to two colours, black and white, based on
    a threshold (24 bit only).

  SQTiling:
    This  operator tiles the image into many blocks. A block size of 10 gives
    a great effect (24 bit only).

@ENDNODE

