     V15.13 (27.6.2008):
     -------------------

     - SV5Objects:   - PNG:        - fixed version string
                                   - upgraded to libpng 1.2.29

     V15.12 (28.3.2008):
     -------------------

     - Library:      - added/improved .cpinfo documentation for various
                       SVOperators, see @{"Preferences" LINK LIB_PREFERENCES }

     - SV5Operators: - Histogram:  - NEWLY added
                                   - two modes
                                   - mode "color":
                                     counts colors of 24/48 bit files,
                                     renders result graphically
                                   - mode "brightness":
                                     like a normal histogram,
                                     but rotated by 90 degrees
                                   - optionally writes textual result
                                     to additional file (e.g. you may parse
                                     it within some other program)
                     - Move:       - NEWLY added
                                   - allows to cut some area and moves it
                                     afterwards to a new location inside
                                     the existing boundaries

     - SV5Objects:   - MIFF:       - NEWLY added
                                   - writes MIFF format as 1..8/24/32/48/64 bit
                                     uncompressed (with alpha/alphamap)
                                   - reading not yet supported (use it in specific
                                     data exchange situations, only)

                     - DDS:        - NEWLY added
                                   - writes DDS (MS DX10) format as 24/32 bit
                                     uncompressed (with alpha)
                                   - reading not yet supported (use it in specific
                                     data exchange situations, only)

                     - JPEG:       - added SPIFF read/write support;
                                     SPIFF is the ITU/ISO successor
                                     of JFIF but yet hardly used
                                     anywhere (I found a website which
                                     claimed to use it for DRM purposes,
                                     but in fact they used JFIF+metadata)
                                   - advantage of baseline SPIFF is, that most
                                     JFIF readers should be able to handle it,
                                     while the additional header really
                                     simplifies file type recognition
                                   - in addition upwards-compatible extensions
                                     of JFIF are defined (e.g. add. colorspaces)

                     - PNG:        - minor optimizations

                     - PSD:        - various significant optimizations
                                   - fixed error-case cleanup
                                   - added CMYK support (import)

                     - MTV:        - fixed internal file info requester title

     V15.11 (21.3.2008):
     -------------------

     - Library:      - fixed possible blitter race condition
                       in V43 pic-dt code for <= 8 bit images

     - Support-Lib:  - fixed possible blitter race condition /w C2P=OS

     - IptcData-Lib: - fixed minor bug

     - ExifData-Lib: - bumped to V2
                     - added binary data handling into current API
                       using a trick (works for V2+)
                     - fixed trailing zeroes issue

     - SV5Operators: - AGA:        - fixed possible blitter race condition

                     - ECS:        - fixed possible blitter race condition

                     - Window:     - fixed possible blitter race condition

                     - Picasso96:  - fixed possible blitter race condition

     - SV5Operators: - AddText:    - fixed possible blitter race condition

     - SV5Objects:   - TIFF:       - added new subtype "TIFF V6.0"
                                     which writes metadata (V5.0
                                     will not write any such data
                                     except copyright strings etc.);
                                     currently this means XML/IPTC
                                   - added new subtype "TIFF EP (ISO)"
                                     which additionally writes EXIF
                                     metadata into the main IFD, which
                                     might contain a thumbnail in
                                     another sub-IFD (V5.0/6.0 will do
                                     this differently). Experimental
                                     and not really EP-compliant yet.
                                   - during loading now determines
                                     the type of TIFF image, which
                                     can be either V5.0, V6.0 or EP (ISO)
                                   - added write support for XMP0/XMP1,
                                     i.e. XMLPACKET (TIFF V6.0)
                                   - added write support for IPTC,
                                     i.e. RICHTIFFIPTC (TIFF V6.0)
                                   - added write support for EXIF,
                                     i.e. EXIFIFD/SUBIFD (TIFF/EP (ISO)
                                     and partially TIFF V6.0); note that
                                     this is experimental (to avoid, do
                                     not write TIPP/EP or switch it off);
                                     currently only works if source
                                     EXIF data is of type "MM" (sorry)
                                   - loaded IPTC data previously was
                                     not correctly byte-swapped if
                                     the source file was in "II" format
                                   - during reading now converts
                                     TIFF EXIF tags into
                                     JPEG APP1-style EXIF marker and
                                     exports this (so that it survives
                                     image conversions e.g. from TIFF
                                     to PNG or JPEG); large tags are
                                     skipped in case this would lead
                                     to exceeding max. APP1 marker size,
                                     e.g. for color profiles;
                                     note that this is experimental
                                     (set READ_EXIF=OFF to disable)
                                   - now reads and writes COPY as COPYRIGHT,
                                     AUTH as ARTIST/SOFTWARE (write: ARTIST),
                                     ANNO as IMAGEDESCRIPTION and
                                     NAME as DOCUMENTNAME (during reading
                                     partially overriden by EXIF/IPTC)
                                   - now respects XMP0 size limit
                                   - now strips trailing linefeeds/CRs
                                     from extracted IPTC tags, if any
                                   - previously, writing 24/48 bit
                                     resulted in files with invalid
                                     end of image directory marker
                                   - previously, writing 24/48 bit /w alpha
                                     resulted in files with invalid
                                     (too small) stripbytecount
                                   - when writing alpha data now also
                                     writing ExtraSamples information
                                   - fixed 1.5kB mem-leak in 8 bit saver code
                                   - added WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF> controlpad

                     - JPEG:       - if IPTC is not present as separate
                                     marker, it will be tried to retrieve
                                     it from within the EXIF marker now
                                   - added WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF> controlpad

                     - PNG:        - added WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF> controlpad
                                   - added READ_EXIF=<ON|OFF> controlpad
                                   - added READ_IPTC=<ON|OFF> controlpad

                     - Printer:    - fixed possible blitter race condition

