     V15.5 (3.2.2008):
     -----------------

     - Support-Lib:  - MOS: fixed viewmode issue from V14.6 again

     - ExifData-Lib: - now uses memory pools, also fixing some compatibility
                       issue with APooler under MOS (see it as workaround)
                       (-> Ingo Schmitz)

     - IptcData-Lib: - now uses memory pools

     - SV5Objects:   - METADATA:   - was writing all supported chunks always;
                                     fixed corresponding bogus metadata dump code
                                   - improved cleanup code (on error)
                                   - added READ support;
                                     creates empty image with metadata
                                     of size [bmhd] or 320x240;
                                     even empty alpha channel is created
                                     if indicated in [bmhd]

                     - BMP:        - also fixed bug in writing 4 bit BMPs;
                                     was introduced in earlier opt. step
                                   - fixed buffer trash issue with 15/16 bit
                                     files; probably introduced in previous release
                                   - fixed buffersize declararion on read (harmless)

     - SV5Operators: - StripAlpha: - now clears alpha field, instead of just
                                     decreasing gfxbuffer version; fixes cases
                                     where version is not checked prior alpha check

     V15.4 (27.1.2008):
     ------------------

     - Library:      - fixed V15.4 history

                     - Datatypes:  - now sets PDTA_Remap at new() time
                                     to avoid problems with some AfaOS versions
                                     (-> Bernd Roesch, indirectly)

     - SV5Objects:   - RGFX:       - writing 32 bit alpha files was broken,
                                     were accidentally written as 24 bit
                                     depth files with 64 pixelbits
                                     (-> Roland Heyder)
                                   - improved detection of faulty files

                                   - smarter error handling

                     - BMP:        - in low memory situations it could have
                                     happened that a failed buffer allocation
                                     caused the source graphics to be left
                                     upside down (-> Roland Heyder)
                                   - changed buffer allocation schemes
                                   - fixed bug in writing 1 bit BMPs;
                                     was introduced in earlier opt. step

                                   - smarter error handling

     - SV5Operators: - Scale50:    - scaling up of 1-pixel width/height graphics
                                     again allowed (just scaling down forbidden)
                                     (-> Thomas Klein)
                                   - changed error code for that case

                     - ScaleFree:  - scaling up of 1-pixel width/height graphics
                                     again allowed (just scaling down forbidden)
                                     (-> Thomas Klein)
                                   - changed error code for that case

                     - Resize:     - scaling up of 1-pixel width/height graphics
                                     again allowed (just scaling down forbidden)
                                     (-> Thomas Klein)
                                   - changed error code for that case

     V15.3 (26.1.2008):
     ------------------

     - Library:      - Datatypes:  - now always sets PDTA_DitherQuality to 0
                                     (-> Thomas Klein, indirectly)

     - SV5Objects:   - SVG:        - 32 bit files were rejected
                                     by the loader (oops)
                                     (-> Thomas Klein)


     V15.2 (20.1.2008):
     ------------------

     - SV5Objects:   - RAW-CM:     - fixed flags

                     - RAW-META:   - NEWLY added
                                   - writes EXIF, IPTC, XMP0, XMP1
                                   - works also if no gfxbuffer set

                     - DEEP:       - saving got broken in svo v8.2 (Dec 2007)
                                     (-> Roland Heyder)

                     - GIF:        - saving got broken in lib v13.7 (Aug 2007)
                                     (-> Roland Heyder)

                     - ACBM:       - saving should be a little bit faster (memory)

     - SV5Operators: - AddAlpha:   - ALPHA_PIXEL24 was wrongly parsed;
                                     did not really work unless it was
                                     0x000000

     V15.1 (12.1.2008):
     ------------------

     - Library:      - bumped version to 15
                     - minimum supported SV5Object version bumped to 8
                     - fixed theoretical (yet not faced) race condition
                       in code for late-adding svo/svd/svp modules

     - SV5Objects:   - METADATA:   - NEWLY added
                                   - writes IFF-AUTH, ANNO, NAME, Copy,
                                     EXIF, IPTC, XMP0, XMP1 according
                                     to what is returned by the original
                                     image loader
                                     see details here @{"IFF-META" LINK SVOBJECT_IFF-META }
                                   - if you want to test it, currently
                                     only loading a JPEG with EXIF/IPTC
                                     data will work (no other formats)

                     - ILBM:       - now sets mskHasAlpha, but with
                                     transparent(Color) := 0

                     - JPEG:       - now fully exports EXIF/IPTC data

                     - YUVN:       - added experimental support for DATA
                                     chunk reading
                                   - added option to switch on/off alpha
                                     reading completely (default is on)

     V14.6 (6.1.2008):
     -----------------

     - Installer:    - default VMEM: dir now Work:T/ instead of T:

     - Guide:        - Copyright bump to 2008
                     - fixed V14.5 history (minor)

     - Docs:         - for .cpinfo added _DIR type which is e.g.
                       required for AdPro.cpinfo

     - Library:      - library priority now set to 1
                     - updated SView5.cpinfo
                     - added AdPro.cpinfo

     - Support-Lib:  - library priority now set to 1
                       with an open count of ca. 150 this may make a difference
                     - build dependency fix
                     - MOS: improved startup code
                     - finally removed vilintuisup.library support in viewmode
                       generation (fallback from cybergraphics) since PicassoII
                       SV5Driver is also gone since a few releases; before, this
                       code was already disabled for MOS (but the library
                       handling code was still there)
                     - now uses memory pools where this is not prevented by
                       API conventions
                     - MOS: fixed long-standing bug in viewmode
                       generation routine (did not effectively occur recently,
                       but may have popped up any time)

     - SV5Objects:   - TIFF:       - optimized some Seek() calls
                                   - files with 16 bit *palette* now explicitely
                                     rejected by internal decoder
                                   - improved handling of bogus files (crash protection)
                                   - improved tag parsing in internal decoder
                                   - in general made it closer to rocksolid
                                   - fixed stupid bug in strip offset parser
                                   - MOS: improved startup code
                                   - upgraded to libtiff 3.8.2 (with 2 of my patches)

                     - GIF:        - MOS: improved startup code

                     - PNG:        - MOS: improved startup code
                                   - upgraded to libpng 1.2.24

                     - JPEG:       - MOS: improved startup code

                     - JPEG2000:   - MOS: improved startup code

                     - RAW-IMPORT: - GRAY8 import did not result
                                     in proper grayscale colormap
                                     (all colors black)
                                   - with 8 bit optionally
                                     a .cm file with a colormap
                                     may be opened (if existant)
                                     thus resulting in LUT8 support
                                     (LUT8 == GRAY8 + LOAD_CM=ON
                                      or      LUT8  + LOAD_CM=ON)
                                   - added dummy FORMAT=LUT8 option
                                     which is same as GRAY8
                                   - file comment now is imported
                                     as "annotation" (and shown e.g.
                                     in SView or accessible via
                                     ARexx); the file comment e.g.
                                     is written accordingly to the
                                     file type when creating raw
                                     data with RAW.sv5object
                                   - now supports LUT8 planar in
                                     addition to LUT8 chunky (prefs);
                                   - for LUT8 planar depth 1..8
                                     is possible
                                   - in case a colormap (.cm) is
                                     available the depth is calculated
                                     from its size (unless larger than
                                     e.g. LUT8 planar size)

     V14.5 (27.12.2007):
     -------------------

     - SV5Objects:   - PNM:        - increased file type check prio
                                   - fixed ID init issue (minor)

                     - MTV:        - optimized file type check code

                     - PICT        - optimized file type check code

                     - Spectrum:   - optimized file type check code

                     - SVG:        - optimized file type check code

                     - SVG-W3C     - optimized file type check code

                     - TIM:        - optimized file type check code

                     - CT:         - bugfixed file type check code

                     - CUT:        - bugfixed file type check code

                     - Unpack:     - added .gz support (using external
                                     gzip commandline tool if in search
                                     path); exceptions are defined
                                     for file types like .tar.gz
                                   - added .bz2 support (using external
                                     bzip2 commandline tool if in search
                                     path); exceptions are defined
                                     for file types like .tar.bz2

                     - JPEG:       - fixed controlpad descriptions

                     - RAW:        - now supports LUT8 chunky in
                                     addition to LUT8 planar (prefs)
                                   - fixed support for writing
                                     Bayer Matrix (Camera CCD sensor)
                                     RAW data (broken in previous release;
                                     it was not 8 but 2x8=16 bit)

                     - RAW-IMPORT: - NEWLY added
                                   - DEVICE SV5Object
                                   - allows RAW import of the following
                                     formats:

                                      - GRAY8   ( 8 bit gray)
                                      - RGB24   (24 bit RGB)
                                      - RGBA32  (32 bit RGBA)
                                      - ARGB32  (32 bit ARGB)
                                      - RGB+A32 (24 bit RGB + 8 bit A) (*)
                                      - RGB48   (48 bit RGB)
                                      - RGBA64  (64 bit RGBA)
                                      - ARGB64  (64 bit ARGB)
                                      - RGB+A64 (48 bit RGB + 16 bit A) (*)
                                      - BAYER8  ( 8 bit Bayer Matrix) (*)

                                    (*) as written by RAW.sv5object

                                   - supports endian conversion for 24 and
                                     48 bit RGB variants, i.e. BGR->RGB (24)
                                     and RGB->RGB (48)
                                   - first you define the endianess, format,
                                     width and height of the file by
                                     controlpad settings
                                   - then you ask to load a file from the
                                     "device", which in turn just opens a
                                     file requester with #?.raw filter,
                                     where you may select a suitable file
                                     for import (can be overriden by
                                     preferences setting, in case of
                                     batch/script usage e.g. from ARexx)
                                   - if the filesize does not match the
                                     given "specifications" it will fail

     V14.4 (25.12.2007):
     -------------------

     - Installer:    - now also installs svmovie, exifdata, iptcdata
                       libraries along with sview5#? libraries
                     - no longer moves Picass96.sv5driver into
                       storage directory prior to copying 030/040
                       versions (would prevent it from being effectively
                       moved); also deletes old version from storage first
                     - now calls "avail flush" at the end

     - IptcData-Lib: - added; based on libiptcdata (see Credits / source)

     - ExifData-Lib: - no longer returns GPS data when there is only the
                       known tag-overlap causing false-positive
                     - general wrapper-fix for GPS coordinate conversion
                       since libexif does not properly handle rationals

     - SVMovie-Lib   - added; compatible to old "svmovie.library"
                       for MovieShop import/export

     - SV5Objects:   - RAW:        - added support for writing
                                     Bayer Matrix (Camera CCD sensor)
                                     RAW data
                                   - added support for writing
                                     YCbCr16 (Video Overlay)
                                     RAW data
                                   - added support for writing
                                     RGB16 (graphics framebuffer)
                                     RAW data
                                   - improved progressbar handling
                                     in some cases

                     - JPEG:       - now supports iptcdata.library
                                     for retrieving of image meta
                                     information
                                   - fixed bug in recognition of
                                     non-standard Mac/Ad*be JPEG
                                     files with .jpeg extension
                                     (.jpg handled correctly)
                                   - added support for reading at
                                     least the JFIF thumbnails
                                     contained in strange PS 3.0
                                     files ending with .jpg
                                   - in most cases the file itself
                                   - EXIF: extra long meta data no
                                     longer able to cause buffer
                                     overflows
                                   - EXIF: fixed GPS coordinate
                                     presence detection (no more
                                     false-positives with empty
                                     information printed)

                     - TIFF:       - now supports iptcdata.library
                                     for retrieving of image meta
                                     information
                                   - now supports exifdata.library
                                     for retrieving of image meta
                                     information

