                                     pixels was not set to opaque

     V13.8 (14.8.2007):
     ------------------

     - Support-Lib:  - 68k:        - assume SetPatch >V43 is true for MOS/OS4
                                     (MOS version already did assume this)

     - SV5Operators: - PagePrint:  - no longer re-uses SV-Library handles;
                                     allocates a fresh one each time instead;
                                     fixes known stability issues

     - SV5Drivers:   - ECS:        - fixed some stupid typo in prefs handling
                                   - behaves more like AGA now (V40 API usage)
                                   - assume SetPatch >V43 is true for MOS/OS4

                     - AGA:        - fixed some stupid typo in prefs handling
                                   - assume SetPatch >V43 is true for MOS/OS4

                     - Window:     - fixed some stupid typo in prefs handling
                                   - assume SetPatch >V43 is true for MOS/OS4

                     - CgxOverlay: - assume SetPatch >V43 is true for MOS/OS4

     V13.7 (5.8.2007):
     -----------------

     - Library:      - optimized SVObject list traversal (seach type/subtype)
                     - minor installer improvement (catalogs)
                       (-> Thomas Klein)

     - SV5Objects:   - GIF:        - killed one more unbuffered read call
                                   - catched one more read failure
                                   - speed improvements by use of
                                     asyncio.library (optionally)
                                   - significant speedup in loading tiled
                                     "true color" images using some caching

                     - MetaView:   - fixed one more Enforcer hit in
                                     local prefs handling code;
                                     in file recognition

                     - AmiIcon:    - fixed one more Enforcer hit in
                                     local prefs handling code;
                                     in file recognition

                     - ILBM:       - fixed one more Enforcer hit in
                                     local prefs handling code;
                                     in file recognition
                                   - fixed Enforcer hit in handle init;
                                     causing hits for read/write operations
                                     (-> Thomas Klein)

                     - TIFF:       - fixed parser bug (possibly)

     - SV5Operators: - AddText:    - array size handling fixed (textlines)

                     - PagePrint:  - string trash issues
                                   - min. fontsize now 8, max. 255
                                   - some fixes

     V13.6 (20.7.2007):
     ------------------

     - Library:      - build script fixes

     - SV5Objects:   - GIF:        - fully reworked GIF parser
                                   - improved error handling,
                                     robustness and stability
                                   - now supports tiled images
                                   - now supports "truecolor" GIFs,
                                     i.e. tiled images with
                                     different (upto) 256 color
                                     palettes now are loaded as
                                     single 24 bit image
                                   - GIF animations are treated
                                     exactly the same way (unless
                                     tiles are turned off, you
                                     always get the last animation
                                     screen as resulting image)
                                   - now supports image disposal
                                     flags (where it makes sense,
                                     i.e. in the context of tiled
                                     images)
                                   - LOCALCOLORMAP controlpad switch
                                     now documented (wonder why not
                                     done before)

                                   - added exhaustive @{"GIF documentation" LINK SVOBJECT_GIF }

                     - CUT:        - v7.x not included due to
                                     build script problem
                                     (-> Roland Heyder)

                     - MTV:        - v7.x not included due to
                                     build script problem
                                     (-> Roland Heyder)

     - SV5Operators: - AddText:    - removed pre-OS3 graphics code
                                   - fixed a race-condition in
                                     MOS recognition code (dangerous)
                                   - removed partially disabled
                                     debugging code fully (for speedup)
                                   - auto-open code for diskfont.library
                                     accidentally got linked due to a
                                     stupid ptr declaration typo
                                   - added additional protection
                                     against some potential rare
                                     "memory freed twice" issue
                                   - disabled some obsolete TmpRas code
                                   - fixed ReadPixelLine8() buf alignment
                                   - other alignment fixes
                                   - optimized memory allocations

                     - PagePrint:  - alignment fixes
                                   - removed partially disabled
                                     debugging code fully (for speedup)

