                                     bogus 0-size chunks

                     - ACBM:       - improved broken file detection
                                   - optimized text chunk reading
                                   - some cleanup in X/Y aspect code
                                   - no more hits in case cmap
                                     allocation fails
                                   - added protection against
                                     bogus 0-size chunks

                     - PBM:        - improved broken file detection
                                   - optimized text chunk reading
                                   - some cleanup in X/Y aspect code
                                   - no more hits in case cmap
                                     allocation fails
                                   - added protection against
                                     bogus 0-size chunks
                                   - generate grayscale cmap if
                                     none present in file (same
                                     as for ILBM/ACBM now)

                     - RGB8:       - improved broken file detection
                                   - some cleanup in X/Y aspect code
                                   - added protection against
                                     bogus 0-size chunks

                     - DEEP:       - improved broken file detection
                                   - added protection against
                                     bogus 0-size chunks

                     - YUVN:       - improved broken file detection
                                   - added protection against
                                     bogus 0-size chunks

                     - PNG:        - upgraded to libpng 1.2.18 (MOS)

     - SV5Drivers:   - CyberGraphics:
                                   - removed EGS7 detection code
                                     and special MOS case;
                                     now cybergraphics.library is
                                     always opened at driver startup;
                                   - also certain side-effects of
                                     the EGS7 detection should be
                                     gone now

     V13.3 (3.6.2007):
     -----------------

     - SV5Objects:   - PNG:        - upgraded to libpng 1.2.18

     V13.2 (23.5.2007):
     ------------------

     - SV5Operators: - EdgeDetect: - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - fixed DIPF handling

                       Sharpen:    - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - fixed DIPF handling

                     - Blur:       - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Convolve:   - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - note, that the "add" parameter
                                     is automatically scaled up
                                   - fixed DIPF handling

                     - ConvolveNxN:
                                   - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - note, that the "add" parameter
                                     is automatically scaled up
                                   - fixed DIPF handling

                     - ConvolveFloat:
                                   - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - note, that the "add" parameter
                                     is automatically scaled up
                                   - fixed DIPF handling

                     - RotateFree: - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Mirror:     - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                   - Y_AXIS/ZEROPOINT did not work
                                     properly in 24 bit mode (color shift)

                     - Mosaic:     - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Scale50:    - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Scatter:    - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Ghost:      - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - ReplaceBorder:
                                   - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - ColorCycle: - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Complement: - now also supports 48 bit graphics

     V13.1 (13.5.2007):
     ------------------
     - Library:      - removed support for the following SV5Drivers:
                       MERLIN, EGS7, Retina, PicassoII
                     - instead, only standard RTG systems like
                       Picasso96 and CyberGraphX are supported
                       from now on (available for most cards,
                       including MERLIN, Retina and Picasso II)
                     - the drivers are not yet removed, but they
                       will no longer be loaded (version too low)
                     - the installer script has been updated accordingly
                     - the corresponding default configs have been
                       removed
                     - removed obsolete .cpinfo files (plenty)
                       from the env directory (requires fresh
                       install to take effect on your system)
                     - fixed SView5.cpinfo
                     - added 48 bit error codes in library and
                       updated all catalogs with corresponding
                       strings (directly derived from identical
                       24 bit error strings)
                     - updated spanish installer strings
                       (-> Damaso Dominguez)

     - SV5Prefs:     - fixed bug in controlpad handling which could
                       have lead to crashes and was memory-inefficient anyway;
                       wizard.library-Bug or in my code (still not sure)


     - SV5Operators: - Cut:       - now allows to select a different
                                    pen (8 bit) or color (24/48 bit)
                                    as background, instead of color #0
                                    or black (0x000000)
                                  - fixed broken dependency in build script

                     - CutInverse:
                                  - added NEW SVOperator
                                  - same as cut, but cuts part of the
                                    graphics and leaves the rest black,
                                    instead of cutting a part (black
                                    afterwards) and leaving the rest

                     - ExtractChannel:
                                  - added NEW SVOperator
                                  - allows to extract single color channel,
                                    i.e. red/green/blue components, as
                                    8/16 bit data for 24/48 bit graphics;
                                    this is different from ExtractRed/
                                    Green/Blue where the result is always
                                    a colormapped graphics (8:8:8 cmap)

                     - ResetChannel:
                                  - added NEW SVOperator
                                  - allows to reset/replace a single color
                                    channel to a given value from 0..255/
                                    0..65535 for 24/48 bit graphics
                                  - if you use "0" as value this allows
                                    for creating the complement of
                                    "ExtractChannel" (R00 + 0GB = RGB)

                     - FlipNibbles:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - here we flip the bytes instead of
                                    nibbles (8:16 instead 4:8)

                     - ScaleFree:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - Resize:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - AlphaBlend:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - FixAlphaBlend:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - fixed bug in ALPHA_PIXEL24 parsing;
                                    now shifted left by 1 byte prior
                                    to interpretation / XOR with alpha;
                                    before, alpha and blue value would
                                    have clashed; only ALPHA_VALUE
                                    would have worked
                                  - USE_SOURCEALPHA was blending
                                    exactly the wrong way (inverse
                                    alpha was used for source); fixed

                     - Antique:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - just scales values down first

                     - Brightness:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - really operates on 16 bit values

                     - Contrast:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - really operates on 16 bit values

                     - RGBAdjust:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - really operates on 16 bit values

                     - Gamma:
                                  - fixed bug with enforced gfxbuf v1
                                    downgrade; resulting in missing
                                    DIPF information sometimes
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics
                                  - really operates on 16 bit values

                     - LeftToRight:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - TopToBottom:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

                     - InvertAlpha:
                                  - now also supports 48 bit graphics

     V12.1 (29.4.2007):
     ------------------
     - Library:      - bumped version to V12 due to further 48/56/64 bit
                       support, i.e. new SVObject/SVDriver flags

     - SV5Operators: - AnyTo48Bit:
                                  - fixed possibly bogus alpha buffer
                                    size calculation
                                  - added brief doc to .guide
                                  - 48 bit flag now set (48 bit worked before)

                     - AnyTo24Bit:
                                  - unified alpha buffer size calculation
                                  - fixed doc in .guide

                     - ExtractAlpha:
                                  - now also supports (8 bit) alpha channel
                                    extraction from 48 bit sources

                     - AddAlpha:
                                  - now also supports adding 8 bit
                                    alpha channel to 48 bit sources

                     - ExtractRed:
                                  - now also supports (8 bit) red component
                                    extraction from 48 bit sources

                     - ExtractGreen:
                                  - now also supports (8 bit) green component
                                    extraction from 48 bit sources

                     - ExtractBlue:
                                  - now also supports (8 bit) blue component
                                    extraction from 48 bit sources

                     - Cut:       - added 48 bit support
                                  - remove some unused variables
                                  - fixed alpha buffer size calculation

                     - Crop:      - added 48 bit support
                                  - remove some unused variables
                                  - fixed alpha buffer size calculation

                     - Scale50:   - added 48 bit support

                     - Rotate:    - added 48 bit support

                     - ExtractGrayScales:
                                  - now also supports (8 bit) grayscale
                                    calculation from 48 bit sources
                                  - fixed bug in GfxBuffer allocation;
                                    i.e. the size was always to large
                                    for > 8 bit graphics, but the external
                                    buffersize declaration was ok
                                  - sort=ascending/descending did not work
                                    properly for 8 bit graphics, in case the
                                    source color depth was not 8 bit
                                  - sort=descending previously was not
                                    implemented correctly
                                  - added sort=none option
                                  - still sort=ascending is default
                                  - sorting now also works for 24/48 bit
                                  - finally documented the "sort" switch

                     - StripAlpha:
                                  - 48 bit flag now set (48 bit worked before)

     - SV5Objects:   - ILBM:      - fixed alpha channel saving in 64 bit
                                    mode; previously the low-byte was
                                    always zero(ed)
                                  - 48 bit flag now set

                     - RGFX:      - fixed alpha channel saving in 64 bit
                                    mode; previously the low-byte was
                                    always zero(ed)
                                  - 48 bit flag now set

                     - PNG:       - 48 bit flag now set
                                  - 48 bit import now default for 48 bit images

                     - PNM:       - 48 bit flag now set
                                  - 48 bit import now default for 48 bit images

                     - PFM:       - 48 bit flag now set
                                  - 48 bit import now default in general

                     - SVG:       - fixed stupid bug in file validity
                                    check during loading; maybe also
                                    caused hits
                                  - wrong bytesperline value was saved
                                    for 32 bit files
                                  - improved bad file recognition
                                  - speed improvements (buffering)
                                  - no longer resets DIPF to 0L with alpha
                                  - previously TypeID was more than 15 byte
                                    long, which caused some trash
                                  - full rewrite of loader code;
                                    fixes some potential crashes
                                  - added support to import/export
                                    48 bit images (or 64 bit with alpha)

                     - TIFF:      - added support for reading and writing
                                    48/64 bit files
                                  - 48 bit flag now set
                                  - alpha flag now set (previously forgotten)
                                  - fixed external buffersize declaration
                                    for > 8 bit graphics

                     - RAW:       - added support for exporting
                                    48/64 bit files

     - SV5Drivers:   - Window:    - 48 bit flag now set

                     - CyberGraphics:
                                  - 48 bit flag now set

                     - CgxOverlay:
                                  - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - Picasso96: - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - AGA:       - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - ECS:       - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - Retina:    - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - PicassoII: - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - MERLIN:    - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - EGS7:      - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

     V11.1 (15.4.2007):
     ------------------
     - Library:      - bumped version to V11 due to 48/56/64 bit support,
                       i.e. new SVOperator flags

     - SV5Objects:   - PNG:       - added support to write 48 Bit images,
                                    as e.g. created via AnyTo24Bit SV5Operator
                                  - fixed a minor memory leak which could occur
                                    with alpha channel images in case of an
                                    internal libpng encoding error
                                  - added support to import 48 bit images;
                                    it needs to be preconfigured in the
                                    controlpad settings if you want
                                    24 bit or 48 bit import of image data
                                  - import of 64 bit (48 bit plus 16 bit alpha)
                                    and export of 64 bit (48 bit plus 8 bit alpha)
                                    is also supported

                     - HDR:       - optimized mem allocation (faster)
                                  - improved error handling
                                  - experimented with 48 bit (difficult)

                     - PFM:       - added support to import 48 bit images;
                                    it needs to be preconfigured in the
                                    controlpad settings if you want
                                    24 bit or 48 bit import of HDR data
                                  - added support to export 48 bit images

                     - PNM:       - added support to import 48 bit images;
                                    it needs to be preconfigured in the
                                    controlpad settings if you want
                                    24 bit or 48 bit import of HDR data
                                  - added support to export 48 bit images

                     - ILBM:      - added support to import/export
                                    48 bit images (or 64 bit with alpha)

     - SV5Operators: - AnyTo24Bit:
                                  - no longer strips the alpha channel
                                    in case the "conversion" is done from
                                    24 bit to 24 bit (preserved now)
                                  - added support to convert 48 bit
                                    to 24 bit (including alpha channel)

                     - AnyTo48Bit:
                                  - NEWLY added
                                  - supports conversion to 48 bit
                                    including alpha channel (48+8)
                                  - yet 16 bit alpha channel is not
                                    supported

                     - PagePrint: - minor internal fix

     - SV5Drivers:   - CyberGraphics:
                                  - prevented some AOS-specific code to
                                    be executed under MOS (EGS fake loader)
                                  - utility.library was not opened, which
                                    could lead to all sorts of funny
                                    problems, esp. when trying to display
                                    a gfx buffer after applying a SV5Operator
                                  - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)

                     - Window:    - added support for displaying 48 bit
                                    gfx buffers (yet using AnyTo24Bit)


     V10.12 (31.3.2007):
     -------------------
     - SV5Objects:   - GIF:       - badly compressing files will
                                    not cause an error so quickly
                                    any more; 125% still valid
                                    (-> Roland Heyder)
                                  - fixed some very broken header file

     V10.11 (22.3.2007):
     -------------------
     - SV5Objects:   - BMP:       - saver got broken due to bug in
                                    new error handling; 8 bit may
                                    have worked, 24 bit surely not;
                                    bug resulting from V10.9 changes
                                    (-> Roland Heyder)

                     - GIF:       - improved error handling once again;
                                    avoid creation of truncated files
                                    (-> Roland Heyder)


     V10.10 (3.3.2007):
     ------------------
     - Library:      - fixed bug in datatype code which would not
                       have recognized the alpha channel under
                       some non-MorphOS systems, especially
                       with pic-dt V45; as consequence, only
                       24 Bit RGB data instead of 32 Bit ARGB
                       would have been imported

     - SV5Objects:   - SVG:       - due to a build error it was
                                    not bumped to v7 (still v6.4)
                                  - therefore it stopped working

     V10.9 (28.2.2007):
     -----------------
     - Support-Lib:  - MOS .elf module was STILL missing

     - SV5Operators: - DitherFix24:
                                  - clear some field in gfxbuffer
                                    even if not relevant for the
                                    used version (defensive)

                     - Dither24Bit:
                                  - clear some field in gfxbuffer
                                    even if not relevant for the
                                    used version (defensive)

     - SV5Objects:   - GIF:       - very poorly compressing GIFs
                                    no longer may crash the encoder;
                                    may cause encode error instead
