     V10.3 (5.2.2007):
     -----------------

     - Docs:         - for .cpinfo added _FILE_ENV type which is e.g.
                       required for loading the new (user) pre-defined
                       convolution matrix files for Convolve

     - SV5Operators: - Convolve:  - optimized mem alloc
                                  - now is able to load convolution
                                    matrix files (path+name)
                                  - included 36 pre-defined
                                    convolution filters;
                                    location is env:sview5-library/Convolve/
                                  - zero divisor no longer accepted,
                                    will be turned into 1

                     - Sharpen:   - optimized mem alloc

                     - Ghost:     - NEWLY added; applie ghosting
                                    effect to image

     V10.2 (4.2.2007):
     -----------------

     - SV5Operators: - Convolve:  - reverted previous b/w change

                     - Sharpen:   - improved algorithm/matrix
                                    (-> Roland Heyder)

     V10.1 (4.2.2007):
     -----------------

     - Docs:         - documented new "AREA" .cpinfo data type, which
                       allows to select an area visually and pass the
                       rectangle coordinates as ControlPad parameter
                       to SV#? modules in form "PARAM=left,top,width,height";
                       e.g. as parameter to Cut/Crop SV5Operator
                     - removed Steve Quartly's old REGION controlpad
                       proposal since it is going to be supersided by
                       the new AREA style approach with SV_AREA being
                       the default controlpad for this; this way
                       older SV modules still may follow the older
                       approach, until it's fully replaced
                     - removed/fixed some outdated/bogus .cpinfo docs
                     - fixed broken links in .guide (e.g. Spectrum/SCR)
                     - added also COLOR_IDX, COLOR_RGB, COLOR_RGB0
                       and COLOR_RGBA types

     - Library:      - added concept of SVHandle-local SVDriver settings
                     - added ability to pass superclass (SVHandle) pointer,
                       still being a black box, down to sub classes (like
                       SVDrivers, SVObjects, SVOperators); it is still
                       strictly prohibited to create kind of self-modifying
                       objects, but it is now possible for them to retrieve
                       additional information on their context
                     - fixed mistake (type) in german catalog

                     - bumped version to 10
                     - minimum supported SV5Object version bumped to 7
                     - minimum supported SV5Driver version bumped to 7

     - Support-Lib:  - added 040 version
                     - applied some fixes to the build scripts

     - SV5Operators: - Crop:      - added SV_AREA controlpad support;
                                    outcommented the separate old
                                    left/top/width/height .cpinfo entries;
                                    however for now they continue to work

                     - Cut:       - added SV_AREA controlpad support;
                                    outcommented the separate old
                                    left/top/width/height .cpinfo entries;
                                    however for now they continue to work

                     - AddAlpha:  - changed .cpinfo in order to allow
                                    specifying pixel and alpha values
                                    separately; simplifies selection
                                    by visual means from a GUI;
                                    old option still available

                     - FixAlphaBlend:
                                  - changed .cpinfo in order to allow
                                    specifying pixel and alpha values
                                    separately; simplifies selection
                                    by visual means from a GUI;
                                    old option still available

                     - ExtractGrayScales:
                                  - made "sorted8bit" controlpad publicly
                                    available and added one more flavour,
                                    to allow ascending and descending sort
                                  - fixed some bugs (and added special
                                    cases) for operations on 1 bit input
                                    graphics (whether b&w or not)

                     - _ALL_ where applicable:

                                  - i.e. Crop, AddText, AutoBorder,
                                         PagePrint, ScaleFree, Resize,
                                         Scale50, ScaleDDA
                                  - now have the "size change" flag set,
                                    so that tools like SView5 can determine
                                    in advance, whether the SV5Operator
                                    will return a GfxBuffer with different
                                    image dimensions as result (or not)

                     - _ALL_ SQOperators:

                                  - added SV_AREA controlpad support;
                                    outcommented the separate old
                                    region/left/top/width/height .cpinfo entries;
                                    however for now they continue to work

     - SV5Drivers:  - _ALL_ SV5Drivers:

                                  - bumped version to 7
                                  - all SV5Drivers now receive and keep
                                    a pointer to their superclass (SVHandle)

     - SV5Objects:  - PNG:        - upgraded to libpng 1.2.15

                    - SGI:        - an alpha channel of a 32 bit image
                                    is no longer stripped, but imported

                    - C64:        - added NEW support for GODOT/4BT 16 color
                                    format files
                                  - replaced palette for Koala, Doodle
                                    with a better one (same colors as 4BT)
                                  - fixed .guide (GEOS was missing)
                                  - slightly optimized file recognition

                    - Targa:      - cleaned up docs in the .guide

                    - DEEP:       - the .guide -wrongly- stated, that
                                    in RLE mode the 8 bit alpha channel
                                    of an 32 bit image was stripped (fixed)

                    - PXR:        - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading P*xar rendering
                                    files in PXR format (24/32 bit)
                                    i.e. with optional alpha channel

                    - CT:         - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading Scitex CT/SCT
                                    pre-press/print format in 8 bit grayscaled
                                    and /24 bit

                    - WBMP:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving WAP Bitmap
                                    (WBMP) files in black & white (there are no
                                    others, BTW)

                    - NEO:        - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading
                                    Atari NEO files with upto 16 colors
                                    in 3 resolutions
                                  - see documentation

                    - QL:         - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading
                                    Sinclair QL files with upto 16 colors
                                    in 2 variants (QL4/QL8)
                                  - see documentation

                    - MAC:        - added write support
                                  - requires ScaleFree and HilbertDither256
                                    svoperators, in case the source graphics
                                    is either of wrong size or depth
                                  - in case the depth matches, HilbertDither
                                    is not applied, but some palette matching
                                    and sorting is done
                                  - improved robustness of PackBits decoder

                    - Degas:      - improved palette conversion;
                                    previously colors were too dark

                    - Spectrum:   - improved palette handling
                                  - now also loads .zx files

                    - SVG-W3C:    - applied some fixes to .cpinfo (config)

                    - _ALL_ SV5Objects:

                                  - bumped version to 7
                                  - all SV5Objects now receive and keep
                                    a pointer to their superclass (SVHandle)
                                  - changed to support and make use of the
                                    new concept of "local" SVDriver settings;
                                    if and where applicable

                    - _ALL_ SV5Objects where applicable:

                                  - hardened & improved file recognition

     V9.2 (24.1.2007):
     -----------------

     - beta release of v10.1 with some missing features of the final
       version (made available only to beta testers)


     V9.1 (14.1.2007):
     ----------------

     - Library:      - bumped version to 9
                     - prior to V9, viewing of a GfxBuffer with a freshly
                       allocated handle would not have worked, if not
                       explicitely set but only passed to the view
                       function (fixed) - there was a bogus error check
                       inside the function not recognizing this case
                     - fixed some catalog texts

     - SV5Drivers:   - CgxOverlay:
                                  - maintenance

     - SV5Operators: - EdgeDetect:
                                  - made it look like other EdgeDetects,
                                    i.e. favour black over white
                                  - uses float instead of double now
                                  - other fixes (improved borders, etc.)
                                  - etc.

                     - Convolve:  - made it look like other "EdgeDetect"s,
                                    i.e. favour black over white
                                  - other fixes (improved borders, etc.)
                                  - no longer opens/links float libs,
                                    since not required (shorter code)

                     - Sharpen:   - something was wrong in the calculation
                                    due to sign errors
                                  - other fixes (improved borders, etc.)
                                  - the sharpness factor now is configurable
                                    by controlpad (-15 to 15; 4-8 is best)

                     - Crop:      - improved error handling for bogus
                                    input parameters

                     - Cut:       - improved error handling for bogus
                                    input parameters
     - SV5Objects:

                     - _ALL_ where applicable:

                                  - the last version of the show()
                                    function did not correctly propagate
                                    window (idcmp and plain) flags;
                                    became visible with latest SView5;
                                    which uses a different approach regardless
                                    of the fix now

     V8.2 (11.1.2007):
     ----------------

     - beta release published to testers, only

     - Docs:         - Guide:     - some minor changes

     - SV5Objects:   - PFM:       - changed fileformat ID strings
                                  - SCALE_FACTOR controlpad did not
                                    work due to double/float mixup
                                    in scanf
                                  - loading of 8 bit "Pf" files
                                    did not work due to the colormap
                                    being fully black (instead of
                                    grayscales)
                                  - added save support for "PF" & "Pf"
                                  - improved error handling

                     - PNM:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - BMP:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - HDR:       - added kludge for HDRIE file
                                    recognition
                                  - disabled debug output
                                  - changed fileformat ID string
                                    to "HDR (RGBE)" since Radiance
                                    is not the only tool writing it

     - SV5Drivers:   - CgxOverlay:
                                  - fixed problem with Window flags
                                    not set as requuested by client

                     - Retina:    - fixed problem with Window flags
                                    not set as requuested by client

                     - Window:    - fixed problem with Window flags
                                    not set as requuested by client

     - SV5Operators: - ChangeColor:
                                  - added new 8 bit SV5Operator for
                                    changing a single color in a palette
                                    by providing colormap index and
                                    #RRGGBB value (0xRRGGBB hex format)

                     - ChangePixel24:
                                  - added new 24 bit SV5Operator for
                                    changing a single color RGB value
                                    by providing old and new
                                    #RRGGBB value (0xRRGGBB hex format)

                     - ReplaceBorder:
                                  - added new 8/24 bit SV5Operator for
                                    replacing the color of a single-colored
                                    frame around an 8/24 bit image
                                    by providing a new
                                    #RRGGBB value (0xRRGGBB hex format)
                                  - note, that those frames may turn out
                                    not to be reactangles with 8 bit images,
                                    in case that palette index is also used
                                    elsewhere (in the other case, the depth
                                    is incremented by one so that there is
                                    no overlap with other areas of the image)
                                  - it makes sense to run "OptimizePalette"
                                    afterwards just to be sure

                     - AutoBorder:
                                  - fixed stupid memory leak: the image
                                    buffer was always allocated twice,
                                    but only used and released once
                                  - not sure when this bug was introduced

                     - ExtractRed:
                                  - did not work correctly in 24 bit mode;
                                    maybe the bug was there since ages but
                                    never triggered before v8.1 (not sure)

                     - ExtractGreen:
                                  - did not work correctly in 24 bit mode;
                                    maybe the bug was there since ages but
                                    never triggered before v8.1 (not sure)

                     - ExtractBlue:
                                  - did not work correctly in 24 bit mode;
                                    maybe the bug was there since ages but
                                    never triggered before v8.1 (not sure)

     V8.1 (6.1.2007):
     ----------------

     - Library:      - bumped version to V8
                     - added a number of new error codes
                     - added german and english texts for new error codes

     - Docs:         - Guide:     - fixed SV5Operator overview page
                                    content and layout
                                  - fixed SV5Driver overview page
                                    content
                                  - added missing info to v6.1
                                    release notes

     - SV5Support:   - now preserves alpha MAP / trans color
                       information (from 8 bit sources)
                       during c2p or p2c conversions(!)
                     - in the same context, fixed a problem in
                       case a gfx with an alpha MAP (e.g. 8 bit PNG)
                       for some reason was converted to bitplane
                       (e.g. when saved as ILBM); memory released
                       twice, under certain circumstances

     - _ALL_ SV Modules:          - made use of new error codes,
                                    where applicable (not all places
                                    fixed/changed yet; still some old
                                    less appropriate codes in use)

     - SV5Drivers:
                     - Window:    - now allows for HAM6/8 display in
                                    case the display window is opened
                                    on a 24 bit screen (HAM6/8 converted
                                    to 24 bit prior to rendering, then)
                                  - this should also work on 16 bit screens,
                                    but was not tested (same algorithm as
                                    for normal 24 bit graphics on 16 bit
                                    screens)
                                  - NOTE: requires AnyTo24Bit SV5Operator
                                    and causes more overhead than e.g.
                                    in CyberGraphics SV5Driver (where this
                                    is done internally, transparently)

                     - CgxOverlay:
                                  - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?!)

                     - PicassoII: - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?!)

     - SV5Objects:   - XPM:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving
                                    XPM v1-v2 (X11) with upto 256 colors
                                  - how do you spell "braindamaged"? ;-)
                                  - see documentation

                     - XBM:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving 1 bit
                                    XBM v10/v11 (X11)
                                  - how do you spell "braindamaged"? ;-)
                                  - see documentation

                     - CUT:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving
                                    Dr. Halo CUT/PAL images
                                  - see documentation

                     - MTV:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving 24 bit
                                    MTV Raytracer files
                                  - see documentation

                     - HDR:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving 24 bit
                                    HDR Radiance files
                                  - see documentation

                     - PFM:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading and saving 24 bit
                                    Portable Floatmap HDR files
                                  - PFM is a floating-point version
                                    of PNM (PPM P6)
                                  - see documentation

                     - MSP:       - NEWLY added
                                  - supports loading 1 bit
                                    MS Paint v1.0/v2.0 files
                                  - see documentation

                     - Camedia:   - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames

                     - GPlot:     - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames

                     - Limbo:     - optimized (mem alloc, stack usage)

                     - WPG:       - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?)
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - checks for unexpected EOF during read
                                    and file recognition
                                  - improved error handling
                                  - added support for v5.0 bitmap headers
                                  - improved crash protection against
                                    brokenly compressed buffers
                                  - added WRITE support for upto 8 bit

                     - FXPaint    - returns external tool error in case
                       StarGate:    of version conflict report now, if
                                    FXPaint is not running
                                  - show() now is just a dummy
                                  - init code became broken during previous
                                    rework (would have rejected access
                                    perhaps)

                     - Printer:   - show() now is just a dummy
                                  - killed a printf() in the Studio error
                                    handling (hopefully not a crash reason)
                                  - optimized (mem & tmp-bitmap alloc)
                                  - fixed a minor memleak (ColorMap 256)
                                    with TurboPrint
                                  - init code became broken during previous
                                    rework (would have rejected access
                                    perhaps)

                     - Scanner:   - init code became broken during previous
                                    rework (would have rejected access
                                    perhaps)

                     - EPS:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - checks for unexpected EOF during read
                                  - fixed bug with missing return code
                                    in show() function
                                  - fixed SVDriver handling code (IDCMP
                                    flags were not propagated, so any
                                    screen/window could not be closed
                                    just by a mouse-click from SView5)

                     - WinIcon:   - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - FBM:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling
                                  - fixed small bug in file recognition

                     - TIM:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - Targa:     - optimized (mem alloc, file recognition)
                                  - improved error handling
                                  - previously the ALPHA flag was not set
                                    for the SV5Object, thus not indicated
                                    to be 32bit-capable in e.g. SView5

                     - Spectrum:  - optimized (mem alloc, file recognition)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - CVP:       - optimized (mem alloc, file recognition)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - CDR:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - uses buffered IO for read/write
                                    calls during load operation now

                     - TIFF:      - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?!)

                     - PCX:       - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?!)

                     - LJPG:      - now uses 16K buffer for IO

                     - QRT:       - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet?!)
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - SunRaster: - optimized (mem alloc, stack usage)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - PBM:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - DEEP:      - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - RGFX:      - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - ACBM:      - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - ILBM:      - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - YUVN:      - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - MAC:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - PCX:       - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - improved error handling

                     - GIF:       - fixed a strcpy to strncpy (harmless)
                                  - fixed LE/BE conversion macro, which
                                    was broken since ages (no effect yet)
                                  - small optimizations
                                  - recompiled with -O3 for MOS
                                  - deleted unused field in priv. lib base
                                  - fixed hits under MOS (see: "ALL...")
                                  - now uses 4K buffer for IO
                                  - optimized mem alloc
                                  - improved error handling

                     - PNM:       - uses larger buffers for read/write
                                    (8K minimum for both, for reading
                                     the value is increased upto 32K
                                     depending on image type/dimensions)
                                  - no longer mixes buffered/unbuffered I/O
                                    during writing

                     - PCD:       - V6.1 introduced a bug into handling of
                                    PCD.controlpad which caused PCD loading
                                    to fail since then (illegal BASE value)
                                    with the infamous "suggest reboot" error
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - fixed problem with spaces in path names
                                  - now uses buffered I/O
                                  - fixed minor bugs in the filename check
                                    of the file recognition code
                                  - replaced file recognition code by
                                    better one
                                  - a number of optimizations
                                  - changed behaviour of some controlpad
                                    settings (see documentation) as well
                                    as the related internal logic
                                  - added new controlpad for forcing usage
                                    of external decoders (i.e. hpcdtoppm)
                                    if wanted
                                  - improved external decoder (hpcdtoppm)
                                    error handling
                                  - embedding of external decoder(s) now
                                    more straightforward
                                  - progress bar properly propagated to
                                    external decoder (i.e. req. SV module)
                                    when active

                     - UltraConv: - now finally disabled, since
                                    obsolete (PMPro relict);
                                    while still physically present,
                                    it is de-facto inactive;
                                    there is no more "animation 1st frame"
                                    support in sview5.library

                     - FastILBM24:
                                  - removed really everything now (<2K)

                     - _ALL_ MOS .elf modules:

                                  - the priv. lib bases were included
                                    separately with different pragma
                                    pack directives
                                  - this could have caused hits in case
                                    fields of this base were accessed
                                    from within the modules (not outside)
                                  - only in case of the GIF .elf module
                                    (not the 68k version) this happened
                                    sometimes (luckily there was an unused
                                    field left which prevented bigger harm)

     - SV5Operators: - FlipNibbles:
                                  - added new SV5Operator for
                                    manipulation of the pixel/component
                                    byte nibbles of possibly broken
                                    images (i.e. saved by broken tool)

                     - InvertAlpha:
                                  - now also inverts alpha MAPs of 8 bit
                                    images (e.g. from colormapped PNG)
                                    and not just alpha CHANNELS of 24
                                    bit images
                                  - if the image previously only had
                                    a *single* transparent COLOR (e.g.
                                    from a GIF), an alpha map with
                                    all colors being transparent
                                    except the formerly transparent
                                    color is added (becomes opaque)

                     - StripAlpha:
                                  - just updated the builtin description
                                    to reflect that alpha channels/maps
                                    and transparent colors are stripped

                     - Antique:   - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - AddTransColor:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - ChangePalette:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - Dither24Bit:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - DitherFix24:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - PaletteDither:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)

                     - EdgeDetect:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc)
                                  - the past few versions were
                                    broken (crash!) due to a
                                    mess with the math libraries

                     - Gamma:
                                  - the past few versions were
                                    broken (crash!) due to a
                                    mess with the math libraries
                                  - also something else was broken,
                                    possibly

                     - HilbertDither256:
                                  - optimized (mem alloc), minor

                     - Sharpen:
                                  - no need for scmffp.lib

                     - AnyTo24Bit:
                                  - now returns v2 buffers (DIPF=0L)

                     - ScaleFree:
                                  - protected against wrong (future)
                                    handling of > v3 gfxbuffers
                                  - in low memory situations, the
                                    alpha buffer ptr from the original
                                    graphics would have been copied
                                    and freed twice, afterwards (sigh)
                                  - SCALE_FACTOR added to .cpinfo
                                    (worked before, but was missing)

                     - Resize:
                                  - protected against wrong (future)
                                    handling of > v3 gfxbuffers
                                  - in low memory situations, the
                                    alpha buffer ptr from the original
                                    graphics would have been copied
                                    and freed twice, afterwards (sigh)

                     - _ALL_ /w alpha & 8 bit support:

                                  - now preserving alpha MAP / trans color
                                    information (from 8 bit sources)
                                    if it makes sense

                     - _ALL_ where applicable:

                                  - now preserving v2 DIPF information
                                    if it makes sense (i.e. always if
                                    the color model remains unchanged)
                                  - no longer resetting v2 DIPF when
                                    creating v3 ALPHA (copy-paste)

                     - _ALL_ where applicable:

                                  - now returning v2 DIPF information
                                    set to 0L instead of v1 w/o

                     NOTE: The DIPF related fixes mainly address
                           potential problems with HAM or EHB graphics,
                           since with any other kind of graphics the
                           DIPF field is not that important. See
                           graphics.library for details on DIPF flags.

     V7.4 (27.12.2006):
     ------------------

     - Docs:         - Guide:     - fixed SV5Object overview page
                                    content and layout

     - SV5Objects:   - PICT:      - now explicitely rejects any
                                    (future) versions above v2
                                  - during writing distincts
                                    between V2.x
                                  - fixed alignment during writing;
                                    previously some files could have
                                    been written with bad alignment
                                    in the last 3 bytes, resulting
                                    in EOF errors
                                  - now supports writing 8 Bit
                                    chunky files, too
                                  - changed file type list again;
                                    only one PICT type available
                                    for selection (24/32 bit
                                    selection done via controlpad)

     V7.3 (26.12.2006):
     ------------------

     - Installer:    - now handles svg2png initial config

     - Prefs:        - fixed a problem with ControlPads and
                       extra chars in paths

     - SV5Operators: - CallPNM:   - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames
                                  - removed unused, but buggy part
                                    of System() call

                     - AddAlpha:  - error return codes were not
                                    propagated from some sub
                                    routine, thus could have lead
                                    to crashes instead of error
                                  - now scales input graphics to
                                    required size, if necessary
                                    (can be switched off, if you
                                     prefer to get an error)

     - SV5Objects:   - IMG:       - added support for GEM XIMG
                                    reading (8/24 bit)
                                  - improved general support
                                  - for XIMG now 8 bit paletted
                                    and 24 bit Truecolor files
                                    are supported (24 bit untested)
                                  - added write supported, either
                                    as 1..8 bit grayscaled IMG
                                    or 1..8/24 bit colormapped/
                                    truecolor XIMG
                                  - fixed a number of bugs
                                  - changed name/type of file
                                    format (only two types left)

                     - ILBM:      - write: fixed cond. mem
                                    leak; if allocation of a very
                                    small buffer failed,
                                    the previously allocated big
                                    buffer would not have been
                                    released anymore

                     - AmiFIG:    - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames

                     - MetaView:  - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames

                     - Limbo:     - fixed problem with spaces
                                    in filenames

                     - Ghost-     - fixed problem with spaces
                       Script:      in filenames

                     - UltraConv: - ".ps" -> ".tmp"

                     - Unpack:    - minor optimizations in .hqx loader

                     - SVG:       - reconstruction due to data loss

                     - SVG-W3C:   - added NEWLY
                                  - added support for Scalable Vector
                                    Graphics - i.e. SVG (W3C)
                                  - requires "svg2png" tool from
                                    e.g. SVGTools package on Aminet
                                    for reading
                                  - optionally, for saving (black &
                                    white shapes in form of) SVG files,
                                    the tool "potrace" from Aminet
                                    is required.

                     - PICT:      - improved serial re-entrancy
                                    behaviour (i.e. next caller
                                    gets clean engine)
                                  - did some optimizations speed-wise
                                  - replaced exotic custom memory
                                    management by memory pools
                                  - added some protection against
                                    memory corruption
                                  - replaced entirely braindamaged(TM)
                                    error handling by setjmp/longjmp
                                  - removed some artificial limitations
                                    in form of fixed on-stack allocations,
                                    which easily could have lead to crashes
                                  - improved memory management in general
                                    (allocate late, release early)
                                  - fixed cond. mem leak; if allocation
                                    of a very large buffer failed,
                                    the previously allocated small
                                    buffer would not have been
                                    released anymore
                                  - improved general out of bounds
                                    checking for dynamic and static arrays
                                  - protection against reading/skipping
                                    zero or negative amounts of bytes
                                  - smarter reading from disk
                                  - fixed bug in file recognition, which
                                    could have lead to rejection of
                                    smaller files
                                  - added proper bound checking in 32 bit
                                    blitting routine
                                  - now properly handles packType 0
                                  - fixed broken opcode 9A handling
                                    (one WORD too much at wrong place)
                                  - added WRITE support for packed 24 Bit
                                    RGB and 32 Bit ARGB files (with optional
                                    alpha channel)
                                  - added READ support for 32 Bit ARGB,
                                    including alpha channel import
                                    (for files where it was not stripped)
                                  - various optimizations

                     - Pictor:    - fixed broken endian conversion macro
                                  - optimized decoder / unpacker
                                  - better crash-protection against
                                    broken files
                                  - fixed bug in file body loader, which
                                    caused artificial file truncation
                                  - files with colordepth = 2 now also
                                    decoded correctly, no longer rejected
                                  - PCPaint v1.0 now explicitely rejected
                                  - PCPaint v1.5 now explicitely rejected
                                  - numerous other fixed and optimizations
                                  - added WRITE support, for packed and
                                    uncompressed files

                     - QRT:       - improved memory management during
                                    save operations (when writing files)

     V7.2 (10.12.2006):
     ------------------

     - SV5Objects:   - LJPG:      - added NEWLY
                                  - incl. docs & credits
                                  - read and write support

                     - RAW-CM:    - added NEWLY
                                  - just saves RAW data
                                  - only saves colormap
                                    (see also RAW)

                     - RAW:       - changed default extension from
                                    .rawpm to .raw
                                  - now also saves alpha channel
                                    in form of a separate chunk
                                    at the end of the file
                                  - now write some basic graphics
                                    info into the file comment
                                  - added documentation

                     - RGFX:      - could have crashed in low
                                    memory situations when
                                    attempting to load 32 Bit
                                    RGBA bitmap
                                  - fixed docs

                     - RGB8:      - previously a wrong FORM
                                    size was calculated when
                                    saving (unpacked 24 bit
                                    instead of packed 32 bit)
                                  - also, in the very worst
                                    case memory trashing was
                                    possible during write
                                  - fixed pot. little bug in the
                                    encoder for byte runs of
                                    exactly 127
                                  - optimized save routine
                                  - optimized read routine
                                  - added alpha channel load/save
                                    support using the "genlock"
                                    bit for boolean alpha
                                    information (0=genlock,
                                    1..255=no genlock)

                     - SVG:       - added 32 Bit RGBA load/save
                                    support (32 bit pixelsize,
                                    32 bit depth = RGBA)
                                  - i.e. alpha channel support
                                  - optimized image loading
                                  - improved error checking
                                    on read operations
                                  - rejects 16 bit and other
                                    unknown file types now
                                  - updated docs

                     - DEEP:      - added 32 Bit RGBA load/save
                                    support (32 bit pixelsize,
                                    32 bit depth = RGBA)
                                  - i.e. alpha channel support
                                    (loading 4/8 bit, saving 8 bit)
                                  - fixed significant memory
                                    leak on RGBA (compressed) import
                                  - optimized decoder
                                  - some minor optimizations

                     - JPEG2000:  - fixed docs (link)

                     - EPS:       - controlpad handling still
                                    was old-style global;
                                    overlooked previously

                     - XWD:       - added documentation
                                  - dropped V10 support
                                  - only V11 supported now
                                  - completely rewritten
                                  - tested with some 8/24/32
                                    bit sample files
                                  - fixed numerous bugs;
                                    the old version was more
                                    or less defunct

     V7.1 (12.11.2006):
     ------------------

     - LIBRARY:      - added AppName support for SV Handle

     - SV5Objects:   - PSP:       - added NEWLY
                                  - PaintSh*pPr* Loader
                                  - supports 1/4/8/24 Bit
                                  - supports uncompressed,
                                    RLE and LZ77 (zip)

                     - PSD:       - #ifdef'ed some (unused)
                                    debug routines

                     - GhostScript:
                                  - fixed crash due to uninit.
                                    output handle (bogus taglist);
                                    esp. occured under MOS
                                  - fixed minor .cpinfo issue
                                  - tested with GS 6.50 only
                                  - finetuned GS settings for
                                    non-printer display

                     - FAXX:      - now is able to load page 1
                                    of multi-page fax files;
                                    previously the file recognition
                                    did not work at all;
                                    CAT chunk support
                                  - also supports exotic CAT
                                    chunks with starting NULL
                                    chunk
                                  - memory allocation for gfxbuf
                                    was bogus (wrong size)
                                  - decoding tables now "const"
                                  - disabled support for
                                    compression type 2,
                                    since those files obviously
                                    are not handled correctly
                                    at the moment (not sure why)

     - SV5Operators: - Cut:       - added "Cut" SV5Operator,
                                    which does the opposite
                                    than Crop (blank cutout)
                     - Mirror:    - added "Mirror" SV5Operator,
                                    which allows to mirror an
                                    input gfx by x-axis, y-axis
                                    or pointwise (zero)
                     - Scatter:   - added "Scatter" SV5Operator,
                                    which allows to scatter an
                                    input gfx by x-axis/y-axis
                                    using a given pixel factor

     V6.6 (25.10.2006):
     ------------------

     - Locale:       - updated a number of spanish translations,
                       including the catalog files (-> Damaso Dominguez)

     - Docs:         - fixed broken IFF-ILBM .guide link

     - SV5Objects:   - ILBM:       - fixed crash which could occur when
                                     attempting to save a 24 bit image
                                     with attached (but ignored) alpha channel,
                                     due to missing version downgrade;
                                     could have caused other problems, too
                                   - 16 and >32 bit files now rejected;
                                     for other depths max. 1 mask plane
                                     is accepted
                                   - added support for loading/saving
                                     32 Bit RGBA, compatible to NewTek's
                                     ILBM extension

                     - EPS:        - removed some redundant, old-style
                                     single-threading code in write code

                     - BMP:        - improved documentation (.guide)
                                   - re-organized whole parser/decoder
                                   - optimizations & bug-fixes
                                   - improved general file(type) recognition
                                   - revised and extended file format defs
                                     in source code (headers)
                                   - fixed RLE4/RLE8 recognition check
                                   - added support for Win95- & NT-style
                                     compression type 3 (16/32 bit)
                                   - do not attempt to convert colormap if
                                     uninitialized due to 16/24/32 bit
                                   - added support for compression type 3
                                     in conjunction with 16 bit; improved
                                     16 bit support for 555/565 formats
                                   - added support for saving 32 Bit
                                     BMP files (Alpha + 24 Bit);
                                     compression type 3 (see docs)
                                   - added support for loading 32 Bit
                                     BMP files (Alpha + 24 Bit);
                                     compression type 3 (see docs)
                                   - applied some formal bugfixes to the
                                     RLE decoder (even though not taking any
                                     effect with known (test) graphics)
                                   - optimized 4 bit uncomp. depacking
                                   - fixed memf flags usage

     - SV5Operators: - InvertColors256:
                                   - fixed textual description

                     - NegateColors:
                                    - fixed textual description

                     - Complement:
                                    - fixed textual description

                     - ColorCycle:  - added NEW SVOperator


     V6.5 (5.10.2006):
     -----------------

     - Docs:         - a little bit of cleanup (still way outdated)

     - SV5Objects:   - UtahRLE:    - now supports reading 8/24 bit,
                                     reading alpha, writing 24 bit

                     - Targa:      - improved file recognition fuzzy
                                     code; more TGA files now accepted
                                     as being valid
                                   - fixed some memory alloc flags

                     - FBM:        - on write, the 1st line was
                                     always garbage/blank, the
                                     last line always missing (fixed)
                                   - did some minor optimizations
                                   - fixed mem-flag usage

                     - AmiIcon:    - rejects HAM format on save now

                     - JPEG2000:   - was not updated in previous release

                     - C-Source:   - bugfixed 68k asm output
                                   - added PPC asm support (GCC)
                                   - added x86 asm support (GCC)
                                   - writing shorter asm lines now,
                                     to avoid line buffer overflows
                                   - tested 68k asm with PhxAss

                     - PSD:        - extension is .PSD, not .PNM
                                   - lots of optimizations
                                   - all SVO flags correctly set now
                                   - now supports reading alpha channel,
                                     for 8 and 24 bit input files
                                   - added read support for 8 bit grayscale
                                   - added read support for 8 bit colormapped
                                   - added read support for 1 bit b&w
                                   - added write support for 8 bit colormapped
                                   - added write support for 24 bit RGB
                                   - supports writing alpha channel,
                                     for 8 and 24 bit input files
                                   - added rudimentary documentation

                     - PNM:        - did some minor optimizations
                                   - fixed mem-flag usage

                     - ALL:        - fixed problem with EHB/HAM check
                                     if the mode ID was INVALID_ID;
                                     did lead to errors usually when
                                     trying to save 8 bit data in
                                     formats where HAM is not supported

     - SV5Drivers:   - ALL:        - fixed problem with EHB/HAM check
                                     if the mode ID was INVALID_ID;
                                     did lead to errors usually when
                                     trying to display data on screens
                                     where HAM is not supported

     - SV5Operators: - 24BitToHAM: - during viewmode transformation/
                                     generation (from 24 bit to HAM)
                                     some old test code was still
                                     active, possibly leading to
                                     an invalid mode ID in rare cases
                     - AnyTo24Bit: - previously any HAM/EHB flags only
                                     were stripped from the viewmode,
                                     but not from the DIPF flags;
                                     could have lead to problems if
                                     some module did not check for
                                     ver >= 2 before checking this
                                     field (ver = 1)

                     - AlphaBlend: - fixed textual description

                     - FixAlphaBlend:
                                   - removed some dead code
                                   - fixed textual description

                     - HilbertDither256:
                                   - fixed "2003" in date string
                                   - fixed __saveds issue

                     - NegateColors:
                                   - fixed __saveds issue

                     - InvertColors256:
                                   - fixed __saveds issue

                     - XOR:        - HAM input now rejected

                     - ALL:        - 8 bit operators:
                                     fixed problem with EHB/HAM check
                                     if the mode ID was INVALID_ID;
                                     did lead to errors usually when
                                     trying to operate on these;
                                     some SV5Operators already included
                                     a fix for INVALID_ID, but also
                                     ignored DIPF then;
                                     all SQOperators had the check,
                                     but it was broken and caused
                                     the routine to exit early
                                     with wrong result (think so)

     V6.4 (24.9.2006):
     -----------------

     - SV5Objects:   - PNM:       - now supports reading P1/P2/P3
                                    and reads more P4/P5/P6 files
                                    than before (improved header
                                    and data decoding)

                     - C64:       - no longer writes ram:dump.txt
                     - RAW:       - now also saves 24 Bit data
                     - UltraConv: - upd. temp. Rexx script
                                  - fixed checks on read (disk)
                     - ILBM:      - no longer attemps to retrieve
                                    x/y aspect from given writescreen
                     - PBM:       - no longer attemps to retrieve
                                    x/y aspect from given writescreen
                     - DEEP:      - written x/y aspect was always 1:1,
                                    now done like for ILBM,PBM,ACBM
                     - RGFX:      - written x/y aspect was always 1:1,
                                    now done like for ILBM,PBM,ACBM
                     - FBM:       - improved written aspect calculation
                                  - written aspect now always is
                                    in floating point format
                                  - included filename now only consists
                                    of file part (without path)

                     - ALL:       - "writes from screen" flag
                                    removed from each SV5Object
                                  - SetWriteScreen/Window made
                                    a dummy call everywhere
                                  - improved error handling in
                                    write function

     - SV5Operators: - AlphaBlend:  - fixed NULL check (blending
                                      against alpha graphics)
                     - AddText      - improved configurability
                     - PagePrint    - fixed .cpinfo
                                    - full internal rework
                                    - now loads any kind of 8/24 bit
                                      image and crops/scales/dithers
                                      it as required
                                    - added rudimentary documentation
                                      including short description on
                                      how to create input "namefiles"
                     - DitherFix24: - 24 bit now dithering against
                                      256 (instead of 252)
                                      colors incl. B&W
                                    - 4 bit now dithering against
                                      16 (instead of 12)
                                      grayscales
                                    - improved dithering to
                                      1..8 / 32..128 colors
                                      (i.e. unequal 16/256)
                                      using better palette
                                    - added rudimentary documentation
                                      including palette description
                                      to .guide file

     - SDK:          - marked SVObject "screen" flags as obsolete/depr.


     V6.3 (10.9.2006):
     -----------------

     - SV5Objects:   - PNG: now uses memory pools internally
                            for libpng


     V6.2 (30.8.2006):
     -----------------

     - LIBRARY:      - fixed a build problem, which possibly
                       affected all 68020+ systems (or all 68k
                       systems) but not MorphOS systems;
                       crashs could occur due to missing
                       sview5support.library V3+;
                       in addition, once successfully started
                       without crash, GIF/JPEG/SQBlur/SQBently
                       would have been missing as V6.x under
                       non-MOS systems
                       (-> Roland Heyder)
                     - released fixed V6.2 modules as hotfix


     V6.1 (28.8.2006):
     -----------------

     - SV5Support:   - bumped to V3

                     - return code of AddControlPad() was always
                       FALSE in case the controlpad did not exist
                       prior to the call (i.e. if no overwrite)

                     - added new function related to local CP
                       finding (i.e. list search, case-insensitive)

     - Library:      - bumped to V6

                     - minimum SV module versions supported: V6+ (all)

                     - cleanup of sample configs

                     - added new parameter to SVL_AllocHandle() for
                       overriding global ENV: settings with local ControlPad
                       content (reserved par. -> now taglist ptr)
                     - added the necessary internal logic (cf. below)
                     - finally introduced tag usage for all handle allocation
                       calls to SVDrivers, Objects and Operators (backward-
                       compatible), too
                     - support for the new LocalConfig tag (and the list
                       behind it) still needs to be added to each single
                       module, which is supposed to make use of this
                       feature
                     - after doing so, it will be theoretically possible
                       for e.g. a batch processing tool and SView5 to
                       run in parallel without having to fear that
                       either one will modify the global ENV settings
                       which the other one does rely on
                     - in addition, the settings processing will become
                       more efficient in the future
                     - also useful for SVObjects/Operators/Drivers which
                       call other such modules internally (i.e. internal
                       "recursion")

                     - [ REMARK 29.12.2006

                         NOTE, THAT _ALL_ SV Modules,
                         i.e. SV5Objects, SV5Drivers, SV5Operators which
                         are included with the Library already were  migrated
                         to the new controlpad preferences mechanism as
                         with Library Release V6.1 ]

     - SV5Drivers:   - AGA:        - fixed bug with uninitialized SVOperatorHandle
                                     attempted being freed after failed handle
                                     allocation with 24 Bit operation
                     - ECS:        - fixed bug with uninitialized SVOperatorHandle
                                     attempted being freed after failed handle
                                     allocation with 8/24 Bit operation
                     - CgxOverlay: - minor fix

     - SV5Objects:   - EPS:       - fixed old re-entrancy issue in write-code (sema)
                     - ILBM:      - renamed DRACO option to IGNORE_CAMG, plus minor fixes
                     - PCD:       - allows to set hpcdtoppm stacksize now
                                  - releases temporary memory earlier now
                     - SPP:       - fixed default extension: .LMB->.SPP
                     - SVG:       - was completely broken in multiple ways,
