  MetaView.sv5object
  -----------------
  This WMF/AMF/IFF-DR2D/DXF/WPG-Vector support module accesses the external
  program "MetaView", which is (C) Henk Jonas.


  HilbertDither256.sv5operator
  ---------------------------
  The description of the "fractal Hilbert dithering" method has been
  found in the "mc magazine, issue 6/94, Franzis-Verlag GmbH".
  The basic techniques (L-System, 16x16 block error approximation)
  are perhaps the same, but the source code as such has been rewritten
  completely in almost any of its parts, so that it has not just
  been "taken out of there" (any limits have been removed; e.g. the
  original source was a standalone-program, which only worked with
  TARGA graphics, which had a width and height divideable by 16, but
  max. 1280x960 or 2560x1920).


  WOS ElfLoader
  -------------
  WarpUP Elfloader (ElfLoadWOS) code originally by Peter Annuss <paladin@cs.tu-berlin.de>
  which it is needed for loading/executing EGCS 2.91.57 WOS PPC binaries under AmigaOS
  (see http://cs.tu-berlin.de/~paladin/ for further information). Has been completely
  rewritten and quite somewhat enhanced and bugfixed in the meantime, though.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CONTROLPAD_FF "ControlPad Fileformat"

  Many SV5Objects, SV5Drivers and SV5Operators have to handle globally set
  preferences, which may also have to be handled and/or modified by
  custom programs or SuperViewPrefs.

  To prevent multiple different ways of storing these preferences
  data, I introduced a common standard fileformat for such configuration
  files: The ControlPad fileformat
  (please read the notes under "Style Guide" below).

   - To allow easy reading and understanding of these files, these are
     stored in plain ASCII
   - To prevent people from learning just another technique of configuring
     files, these are constructed just like a kind of "tooltype lists"
   - a single ControlPad takes a full line of the file
     and looks like that : <Name>=<Content> or <keyword>
     Content and Name may contain any ASCII characters except "=", because
     the first "=", which is found, is used to separate the Name from the
     Content in the line. A keyword is anything, which does not contain
     a "=" somewhere, but is not a comment.
   - So all other special characters are possible (although you should
     not make too much use of them for ergonomical reasons).
   - it is supported to write as much comments to the files, as wished.
     A comment line has to begin with "/" or ";" in its first column.
     A totally blank line fits to the same category as "/" or ";" lines.
   - any single line should not exceed 255 characters


  Additional Notes
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  * Note, that comments are safely read and written by the current
    library version.

  * The SVSUP_FindControlPad() function is case-sensitive, so if nothing
    else is specified, the ControlPad entries are always also
    case-sensitive. Case-insensitive functions already have been added
    (SVSUP_FindControlPadNoCase()) but are not used widely yet.

    By using GUI-based functions for ControlPad modifications which
    prevent the user from changing them directly, you may be able to
    avoid such conflicts.


  Style Guide
  ~~~~~~~~~~~
  Common "style guide" rules (PLEASE NOTE) :

   - ControlPads should be located in "ENV:SView5-Library/"
     and have the plain name of the SV5Driver/SV5Object/... plus
     ".controlpad" as extension.
     For example a ControlPad for JPEG.sv5object should be
     named "ENV:SView5-Library/JPEG.controlpad".
   - for boolean entries use <YES|NO> choices, not <TRUE/FALSE>
     or just set single keywords like "USE_..."
   - for switches, <ON|OFF> choices are most often preferable
     against setting single keywords for either "on" or "off"
   - use pregnant and verbose names for multiple-choices, like
     <HUFF|LWZ|ENTROPY>, not <1|2|3>
   - use short names and statements, not long and complicated ones :
     "ColorDepth=24" instead of "Number_of_Colors=16.7_million"


  Examples
  ~~~~~~~~
  In "Programmers/C-Language/Example_Tools/ControlPad" you find some example
  sources, which deal with ControlPads and should explain anything
  you need to know about these.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CPINFO_FF "CPInfo Fileformat"

  Some applications might wish to enable the user to interactively
  specify controlpad settings just when reading, writing or
  processing an image and not before or after by setting preferences.

  Until this will be managed by sview5.library, sview5support.library
  or the single modules by introducing new functions for handling this,
  applications may take this information from ".cpinfo" files, where
  the specific ControlPad entries are dynamically described.

   Content
   =======
    - Structure in general
    - Structure in detail
    - Structure Entry Description in detail
    - Examples
    - Last Words and Exceptions
    - Future
    - Special configuration Standards


  Structure in general
  --------------------
  Every CPInfo-File is constructed like an usual ControlPad file,
  but in this case, the _order_ of the entries becomes meaningful.
  These files are separated into SECTIONs, where any necessary
  information about specific ControlPad entries are stored.

  To allow easy enhancements and improvements on this format, there's
  an important note:

      - the number of sections is not limited
      - each SECTION _must_ contain at least the entries described below
      - each SECTION _may_ contain more entries, so that it might be
        necessary to skip all the following entries until another "SECTION"
        entry will be reached
      - the order of the entries is _fixed_
      - if any of the following _needed_ entries makes no sense,
        it will still be present as a "dummy", thus just a keyword
        is placed there and no value is given via "="
      - any single line should not exceed 255 characters
      - as with usual ControlPad files, comments and blank lines are allowed

  Structure in detail
  -------------------
      CPINFO                               ; identification
      SECTION=<Name of ControlPad entry>   ; the name of the entry
      TYPE=<INTEGER|FLOAT|ASCII            ; type of data
            AREA|COLOR_xxx|NONE> (*)       ; (signed or unsigned for
                                           ;  INTEGER or FLOAT may
                                           ;  be detected via MIN and MAX).
                                           ; NONE is used for keywords.
      MIN=<Value>                          ; - minimum value for numbers
                                           ; - minimum length for strings
                                           ; - or empty ("MIN")
                                           ; Empty with keywords.
      MAX=<Value>                          ; - maximum value for numbers
                                           ; - maximum length for strings
                                           ; - or empty ("MAX")
                                           ; Empty with keywords.
      DEFAULT=<Default value for entry>    ; what will be used if nothing
                                           ; is specified ?!
                                           ; Empty e.g. with keywords.
      DESCRIPTION=<descriptive text>       ; what does it do ?
      MASK=<input mask>                    ; this one allows to separate
                                           ; choices and "free" enterings
                                           ; Empty with keywords.
      WHEN=<READ|WRITE|ALWAYS|PREFS|NEVER> ; ask for it, when the user
                                           ; does reading or writing
                                           ; (SV5Objects) ? Or always
                                           ; (SV5Drivers/SV5Operators) ?
                                           ; Or never ? (Undocumented)
                                           ; Or Just handle it as a real
                                           ; preferences thing ?

      (*) COLOR_IDX=<0..255>               ; integer in rage 0..255 (8 bit)
          COLOR_RGB=<0xhhhhhh>             ; hex 24 bit color value, e.g. 0xAABBCC
          COLOR_RGB0=<0xhhhhhh00>          ; hex 32 bit color value (last byte 0)
          COLOR_RGBA=<0xhhhhhhFF>          ; hex 32 bit color value (last byte dynamic,
                                           ; but 0xFF by default)


    Atomic Data Types
    -----------------
    INTEGER and FLOAT are considered atomic data types.

    The exact range of the data type (short vs. long or float vs. double)
    can only be determined by the help of the MIN and MAX values.

    Example: "FLOAT_VALUE=0.5"
             "INT_VALUE=16"
             "COLOR_IDX=0"

    Combined Data Types / Arrays
    ----------------------------
    AREA and ASCII are considered to be combined datatypes or arrays.

    AREA consists of exactly 4 INTEGER values being separated by
    comma. These 4 values describe the dimensions / oordinates of a
    rectangle in form of left edge, top edge, No MIN or MAX values are
    taken into account here, since it is assumed that these usually
    depend on an already loaded graphics buffer. The inherent maximum
    range for each value is supposed to be within [0..32767].

    For SV5Operators, SV5Objects or SV5Drivers which allow to specify
    a certain region as "subject" for being worked on, this region
    always should be called "SV_AREA". Any additional area parameters
    do not need to follow a specific naming scheme.

    Example: "SV_AREA=0,0,640,256"

    ASCII comprises an array of UBYTE values, which are used to
    form an array of the same type with resulting length. No control
    codes are allowed, therefore the array normally should not contain
    any.

    Example: "STRING=Here we go!"

    Example: COLOR_RGB, COLOR_RGB0 and COLOR_RGBA

    These can be interpreted either as hex-byte array with a single
    "0x" prefix or as hexadecimal number.

    Structure Entry Description in detail
    -------------------------------------
    o A few words to the MASK entry:

      Any entries which don't have a specific meaning (just comments)
      or mutual exclude entries do have to begin with "<" and end with
      ">". Anything else are control sequences, qhich either are
      to be supported or have to be ignored.

      a) "<...>" or "<...|...|...>"

      Usually you should print out this text as a little help for
      the user, how to enter the data, e.g. into a string/integer gadget.
      But if the string included by "<" and ">" does contain one or
      more "|" these are meant as exclusice choices, which e.g.
      might be represented as mx-, cycle- or listview-gadgets.
      So you may a) present this mask to the user while editing a
      string/integer gadget or b) parse it and just "filter" the input
      via supplying appropriate input gadgets.
      Please note, that the "MIN" and "MAX" values (if specified)
      still have to be valid for this input (if the file definition
      has been done correctly ;-)
      So for a "MASK=<8|24>" these would equal "MIN=8" and "MAX=24".
      But note, that this "mask" is not really meant to define ranges
      with gaps, like "anything between 5 and 37, but except the numbers
      between 33.3 und 36.5" 8-)

      b) Control Sequences

      MASK=_SVOBJECT                means, that a file from "LIBS:sv5objects"
                                    has to be requested, which matches
                                    "#?.sv5object".
      MASK=_SVDRIVER                means, that a file from "LIBS:sv5drivers"
                                    has to be requested, which matches
                                    "#?.sv5driver".
      MASK=_SVOPERATOR              means, that a file from "LIBS:sv5operators"
                                    has to be requested, which matches
                                    "#?.sv5operator".
      MASK=_FILE                    a file to be selected e.g. fromout a
                                    requester (it is supposed, that the user
                                    does the right choice).
      MASK=_DIR                     a directory to be selected e.g. fromout a
                                    requester (it is supposed, that the user
                                    does the right choice).
      MASK=_FILE_ENV                a config file to be selected e.g. fromout a
                                    requester (it is supposed, that the user
                                    does the right choice). The default path
                                    here is ENV:SView5-Library/[module]/ - i.e.
                                    this is useful for loading sub-configurations.

    Examples
    --------

    An entry for a keyword might look like this:

    SECTION=OPTIMIZED_PALETTE
    TYPE=NONE
    MIN
    MAX
    DEFAULT
    DESCRIPTION=Save with optimized palette
    MASK
    WHEN=PREFS


    An entry for a float value:

    SECTION=SCALE_FACTOR
    TYPE=FLOAT
    MIN=0.1
    MAX=2.0
    DEFAULT=1.0
    DESCRIPTION=Factor for scaling graphics
    MASK=<Value>
    WHEN=ALWAYS


    An entry for an ASCII text:

    SECTION=PACKMETHOD
    TYPE=ASCII
    MIN=4
    MAX=4
    DEFAULT=NUKE
    DESCRIPTION=How to pack the written data
    MASK=<XPK-Packer>
    WHEN=WRITE


    An entry for an AREA describing a rectangle:

    SECTION=SV_AREA
    TYPE=AREA
    MIN
    MAX
    DEFAULT
    DESCRIPTION=Area to crop
    MASK=<Value>
    WHEN=ALWAYS


    An example for an ignoreable keyword:

    SECTION=DEBUGMODE
    TYPE=NONE
    MIN
    MAX
    DEFAULT
    DESCRIPTION=Enables debugging mode with Confirm-Requesters
    MASK
    WHEN=NEVER


  Last Words and Exceptions
  -------------------------
  So you see, that it's easy to describe any of the existing ControlPad
  variations this way.

  The "WHEN" statement is a help for applications to decide, whether
  and when to allow changing of specific ControlPad entries.

  Applications should either ignore entries of type "WHEN=NEVER"
  or prepared to handle slightly differing entries, like
  e.g. TYPE=INTEGER entries with a non-set default value.
  (An example had been the "AVAILMEM" switch of interim versions
   of JPEG.sv5object - which was both: a keyword and a common setting,
   but should never be changed during runtime.)

  "WHEN=NEVER" is just for options with experimental state or
  debugging purposes.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CONTROLPAD_LIST "ControlPad Overview"

  ============================================================================
  MAIN LIBRARIES
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/LIBRARY.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - DEFAULTSVDRIVER=<#?.sv5driver>
                          ; Which SV5Driver should be set, when
                          ; SView5-Library is being initialized ?
                          ; For example: "DEFAULTSVDRIVER=AGA.sv5driver"
                        - REMEMBER_CURRENT_PATH=<ON|OFF>
                          ; If set, SView5-Library internally will keep track
                          ; of the path settings for non-DEVICE SV5Objects so
                          ; that other modules (e.g. DEVICE SV5Objects) can
                          ; utilize this information for similar or different
                          ; purposes (e.g. as default path within file
                          ; requesters or for retrieving the original source
                          ; file's path while currently working on VMEM:)
                          ; Default: ON
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/sview5support.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - C2P=<OS|SV>
                          ; determines, whether chunky to planar conversion
                          ; is managed via the appropriate OS functions
                          ; or via internal ones.
                          ; Due to various problems with the OS functions
                          ; "SV" is now default.
                          ; Be careful when using "OS" with GfxCards,
                          ; which carelessly patched graphics.library.
                          ;
                          ; NOTE: PPC code will automatically be utilited,
                          ;       when a PPC is available, but only with
                          ;       C2P=SV
                          ;
                          ; Default: SV
                        - MODEGEN=<OS|SV|SVEXT>
                          ; determines, whether viewmode generation should
                          ; rely on internal/OS functions only, or make
                          ; use of P96/CGfx(/PII) functions when available.
                          ; Similar to ModeP. "SV" may cause problems on
                          ; some systems, may work fine on others.
                          ; "SVEXT" is known from the ak-datatypes series.
                          ; Note: applicable for OS 3.0 and beyond, only.
                          ; Default: OS
  ============================================================================
  SVOBJECTS
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AmiFIG.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling GPlot,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - AMIFIG_PATH=<fig2dev command path plus name>
                          ; how fig2dev is to be called
                          ; e.g. AMIFIG_PATH=Work:AmiFIG/fig2dev
                          ; default is: fig2dev
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AmiIcon.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ICON_DEPTH=<colordepth>
                          ; Depth of icon to be saved.
                          ; Also: WB (depth=2-3, 4-8 colors) or
                          ; MagicWB (depth=4, 16 colors) ?
                          ; default is: 2
                        - ICON_TYPE=<DISK|DRAWER|TOOL|PROJECT|GARBAGE>
                          ; Type of icon to be saved.
                          ; default is: PROJECT
                        - ICON_TOOL=<program name>
                          ; The default tool of the icon to be saved.
                          ; default is: "InsertHere"   ;)
                        - WRITE_NEWICON=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Write NewIcons, when there is newicon.library
                          ; available ?
                          ; Default is: ON
                        - READ_SUPPORT=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Allow reading of icons at all ?
                          ; Default is: OFF
                        - LOAD_WHICH=<OS_31|OS_35>
                          ; Read OS 3.5 or Standard/NewIcon content ?
                          ; (if there's no OS 3.5 content, OS_35 will
                          ;  automatically fall back to Standard/NewIcon
                          ;  content, when available and allowed)
                          ; Default is: OS_35
                        - WHICH_SIDE=<NORMAL|SELECTED>
                          ; Load the normal or selected side of the icon ?
                          ; Default is: NORMAL
                        - SAVE_WHICH=<OS_31|OS_35>
                          ; With WRITE_NEWICON=ON, OS_31 will only write
                          ; the Standard+NewIcon, while OS_35 will rewrite
                          ; the whole icon again as OS 3.5 icon, but
                          ; keeping the NewIcon part (thus writing a
                          ; double-style icon). Filesize will increase.
                          ; Default is: OS_35
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Camedia.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling Camedia,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - CAMEDIA_PATH=<camedia command path plus name>
                          ; how camedia is to be called
                          ; e.g. CAMEDIA_PATH=Work:Camedia/Camedia
                          ; default is: camedia
                        - PICNUMBER=<number of picture>
                          ; which picture (identified by number)
                          ; should be imported from the camera ?
                          ; default is: 1
                        - DEVICE=<Name of serial device>
                          ; UNIT and SPEED *must* be specified, too
                        - UNIT=<unit of serial device>
                          ; DEVICE and SPEED *must* be specified, too
                        - SPEED=<9600..115200>
                          ; DEVICE and UNIT *must* be specified, too
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/DCRAW.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling dcraw,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 524280
                        - DCRAW_PATH=<dcraw command path plus name>
                          ; how dcraw is to be called
                          ; e.g. DCRAW_PATH=Work:DCRAW/dcraw
                          ; default is: dcraw
                        - PICNUMBER=<0..99>
                          ; which picture (identified by number)
                          ; should be imported from the raw file?
                          ; default is: 0
                      : - EXTRACTMODE=<IMAGE|PREVIEW>
                          ; Determines, whether the preview image or
                          ; the full size image part should be extracted
                          ; default is: IMAGE
                      : - FORMAT=<8BIT|16BIT>
                          ; Determines, whether 8 bit (24 bit) or 16 bit (48 bit)
                          ; image raw data should be extracted
                          ; default is: 8BIT
                      : - METAFORMAT=<PPM|TIFF>
                          ; Determines, whether to use PPM or TIFF as vehicle
                          ; for importing the raw image data; TIFF may allow for
                          ; meta data import in the future as well (depends on dcraw)
                          ; default is: PPM
                      : - COLORSPACE=<RAW|SRGB|ADOB|WIDE|PRO|XYZ>
                          ; Determines, which color space to use when importing raw
                          ; data - note, that this option only makes sense with
                          ; METAFORMAT=TIFF and not all options may be fully supported.
                          ; It is recommended to use RAW or SRGB.
                          ; default is: RAW
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/EPS.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - EXTRACTMODE=<HEADER|PS>
                          ; Determines, whether the preview image or
                          ; the Postscript (TM) part should be extracted,
                          ; while parsing the Postscript (TM) part requires
                          ; a working Ghostscript installation with
                          ; GhostScript.sv5object being correctly configured
                          ; default is: HEADER
                        - NO_EPS_HEADER
                          ; if this option is set, the EPS file will be
                          ; written without EPS header, thus turn into a
                          ; plain P*stscript file; useful for sending
                          ; it directly to the printer or for use with
                          ; FinalWriter, WordWorth, TurboPrint
                        - SAVE_ROTATE=<ON|OFF>
                          ; by default, the picture seems to be rotated
                          ; with Postscript (TM) output of this module.
                          ; Enabling SAVE_ROTATE will again re-rotate it to
                          ; the original position.
                          ; default is: OFF
                        - SAVE_CENTER=<ON|OFF>
                          ; centers the images on the page with the
                          ; desired size of SAVE_WIDTH x SAVE_HEIGHT (or not)
                          ; default is: ON
                        - SAVE_RLE=<ON|OFF>
                          ; allows to apply RLE compression to the
                          ; PS output
                          ; default is: OFF
                        - SAVE_DPI=<value>
                          ; DPI value to use for the output
                          ; default is: 300
                        - SAVE_WIDTH=<value>
                          ; Width of the PS page
                          ; default is: 612
                        - SAVE_HEIGHT=<value>
                          ; Width of the PS page
                          ; default is: 762
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ExifTool.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling exiftool,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 65536
                        - PERL_PATH=<perl command path plus name>
                          ; how perl is to be called
                          ; e.g. PERL_PATH=ADE:bin/perl
                          ; default is: ADE:bin/perl
                        - EXIFTOOL_PATH=<exiftool script path plus name>
                          ; how ExifTool is to be called
                          ; e.g. EXIFTOOL_PATH=Work:ExifTool/exiftool
                          ; default is: exiftool
                        - LOADNAME=<filename>
                          ; File to load (suppress file requester)
                          ; use this if you write an ARexx script
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/GhostScript.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling GhostScript,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 131072
                        - GS_PATH=<gs command path plus name>
                          ; how GhostScript is to be called
                          ; e.g. GS_PATH=Ghostscript:gs000
                          ; default is: gs
                        - OUTPUTMODE=<PNG256|PNG24BIT|OTHER>
                          ; Output file format to be used
                          ; (-sDEVICE parameter of Ghostscript's gs).
                          ; Only PNG supported yet.
                          ; default is: PNG256
                        - OTHER_OUTPUTMODE=<pcxmono|pcxgray|pcx16|pcx256|
                                            pcx24b|tiffcrle|tiff24nc|
                                            pngmono|pnggray|png16|png256|
                                            png16m|bmpmono|bmp16|bmp256|
                                            bmp16m>
                          ; If OUTPUTMODE=OTHER has been set, the string
                          ; specified here will directly be passed as
                          ; Ghostscript's "-sDEVICE" parameter
                          ; default is: png256
                        - DPI=<value>
                          ; DPI value to use for the converted output
                          ; (-r parameter of GhostScript's gs)
                          ; default is: 72
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/GPlot.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling GPlot,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - GPLOT_PATH=<gplot command path plus name>
                          ; how gplot is to be called
                          ; e.g. GPLOT_PATH=Work:GPlot/GPlot
                          ; default is: GPlot
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ILBM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ANIM_BODIES
                          ; if set, ANIM files' ILBM-BODY chunk
                          ; (first frame) will be extracted when
                          ; such a file is encountered. Otherwise
                          ; anim.datatype may do that task later.
                          ; (not actually IFF-ILBM support: it's
                          ;  IFF-ANIM support)
                        - IGNORE_CAMG
                          ; tries to avoid possible problems on
                          ; the Draco/Pegasos computer (modeid generation)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/JPEG.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands :   ;
                          ; STANDARD settings
                          ; *****************
                        - READ_MODE=<IMAGE|THUMBNAIL
                          ; Read image or thumbnail (e.g. with EXIF)?
                          ; Disables SCALING for thumbnail, returns
                          ; standard image (eventually scaled) if no
                          ; thumbnail present.
                          ; default: IMAGE
                        - COLORDEPTH=<8|24>
                          ; For READING colored 24 bit images:
                          ; should the output be done as 8 or 24 bit Data ?
                          ; default is 24 Bit data. Grayscaled graphics
                          ; will _always_ be exported as 8 Bit
                          ; default: 24
                        - QUANTIZATION=<0..100>
                          ; For WRITING 8/24 bit images as 24 bit JPEG:
                          ; 0   - poor quality, big compression
                          ; 100 - best quality, no compression
                          ; never use such extreme values, but try
                          ; something like 20, 50, 75
                          ; default is: 75)
                        - READ_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Read EXIF data?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Write EXIF data?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - READ_IPTC=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Read IPTC data?
                          ; default is: ON
                          ;
                          ; ADVANCED settings
                          ; *****************
                        - FORCE_GRAY_DECODE
                          ; For READING images:
                          ; this switch overrides the selected depth
                          ; for colored images and always exports them
                          ; as 8 Bit grayscaled pictures
                          ; default is: not set
                        - DECODE_METHOD=<FAST_INTEGER|SLOW_INTEGER|
                                         FLOATING_POINT>
                          ; For READING images:
                          ; how to DECODE the 24 bit or gray data
                          ; default is: FAST_INTEGER
                        - DITHERMODE=<DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG|
                                      NO_DITHERING|DITHER_ORDERED>
                          ; For READING and dithering 24 bit images
                          ; to 8 Bit images:
                          ; how and whether to DITHER the 24 bit data
                          ; default is: DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG
                        - COLOR_QUANTIZING=<FAST|SLOW>
                          ; For READING and dithering 24 bit images
                          ; to 8 Bit images:
                          ; whether to QUANTIZE the 24 bit data within
                          ; two passes (not with DITHER_ORDERED)
                          ; default is: SLOW
                        - UPSAMPLING=<ON|OFF>
                          ; For READING and dithering 24 bit images
                          ; to 8 Bit images:
                          ; whether to do fancy upsampling on the 24 bit
                          ; default is: ON
                        - FORCE_GRAY_ENCODE
                          ; For WRITING images:
                          ; this switch causes grayscales to be written
                          ; no matter, whether the input was colored
                          ; default is: not set
                        - ENCODE_METHOD=<FAST_INTEGER|SLOW_INTEGER|
                                         FLOATING_POINT|FASTEST_INTEGER>
                          ; For WRITING images:
                          ; how to ENCODE the 24 bit or gray data
                          ; default is: FAST_INTEGER
                        - OPTIMIZE=<ON|OFF>
                          ; For WRITING 24 bit images:
                          ; whether to optimize the generated huffman
                          ; code (good compression, but slow)
                          ; default is: OFF
                        - PROGRESSIVE=<ON|OFF>
                          ; For WRITING 24 bit images:
                          ; whether to write progressive JPEG files
                          ; default is: OFF
                          ; HIGHLY ADVANCED settings
                          ; ************************
                          ; 3 more settings for scaling & threshold
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/JPEG2000.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands :   ;
                        - JAS_JP2_ENC_OPTS=<key=value key=value ...>
                          ; JP2 encoder options (Jasper syntax)
                        - JAS_PGX_ENC_OPTS=<key=value key=value ...>
                          ; PGX encoder options (Jasper syntax)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Limbo.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling GPlot,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - LIMBO_PATH=<Limbo command path plus name>
                          ; how Limbo is to be called
                          ; e.g. LIMBO_PATH=Work:Limbo/Limbo.68030.881
                          ; default is: Limbo.68000
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/MetaView.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling MetaView,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - METAVIEW_PATH=<MetaView command path plus name>
                          ; how MetaView is to be called
                          ; e.g. METAVIEW_PATH=Work:AMF/MetaView
                          ; default is: MetaView
                        - FIG_SUPPORT
                          ; if this keyword is set, AmiFIG.sv5object will
                          ; be overriden and instead MetaView will be
                          ; utilized for imporint FIG drawings
                        - CGM_SUPPORT
                          ; if this keyword is set, GPlot.sv5object will
                          ; be overriden and instead MetaView will be
                          ; utilized for imporint CGM graphics
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/NETPBM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling dcraw,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 65536
                        - NETPBM_PATH=<netpbm command path>
                          ; folder from where NetPBM is to be called
                          ; e.g. NETPBM_PATH=Work:NetPBM/
                          ; default is: c:
                        - REQUEST_LOADER
                          ; if this option is set, the user is always
                          ; asked which NetPBM tool is to be used,
                          ; e.g. giftopnm
                        - NETPBM_LOADER=<netpbm command name>
                          ; NetPBM tool to be called
                          ; default is: giftopnm
                        - NETPBM_LOADER_OPTIONS=<netpbm command options>
                          ; options for NetPBM tool to be called
                          ; default is: <none>
                        - LOADNAME=<filename>
                          ; File to load (suppress file requester)
                          ; use this if you write an ARexx script
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PCD.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - OUTPUTFORMAT=<BASE/16 | BASE/4 | BASE
                                      | BASE*4  | BASE*16>
                          ; specifies the output resolution to be used
                          ; default: BASE
                        - EXTERNAL_DECODER=<ABOVE_BASE|ALWAYS>
                          ; Use external decoder when?
                          ; default: ABOVE_BASE
                        - HPCDTOPPM_PATH=<hpcdtoppm command path plus name>
                          ; how NetPBM's hpcdtoppm is to be called
                          ; e.g. HPCDTOPPM_PATH=Work:NetPBM/ppm/hpcdtoppm
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PICT.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - WRITE_ARGB
                          ; Write 32 Bit ARGB instead of 24 Bit RGB?
                          ; Default: (not set)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PFM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SCALE_FACTOR=<float value>
                          ; Linear brightness adjustment factor
                          ; Range:   16.0 - 1024.0
                          ; Default: 255.0
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PNG.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PNG8_TRANSPARENCY=<ON|OFF>
                          ; whether 8 Bit PNGs should contain
                          ; transparency information
                          ; Default: OFF
                        - PNG8_TRANSPARENT_COLOR=<0..255>
                          ; Default color to be enabled and set
                          ; (graphics control extension block)
                          ; Default: 0
                        - Z_COMPRESSION=<0..9>
                          ; allows changes in compression/speed.
                          ; 0 results in uncompressed data, 9 compresses
                          ; best, but increases decompression time.
                          ; Default: 6
                        - SAVE_INTERLACED=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Save image as interlaced (progressive) ?
                          ; Default: OFF
                        - READ_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Read EXIF data?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Write EXIF data?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - READ_IPTC=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Read IPTC data?
                          ; default is: ON
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PAM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SUPPRESS_HEADER
                          ; setting this keyword will suppress
                          ; writing the PAM header for P7
                          ; files, which actually will generate
                          ; a RAW data file, which cannot be loaded
                          ; with sview5.library again, but may be
                          ; used for different purposes
                          ; Default: (not set)
                        - COLORDEPTH=<24/48>
                          ; Import/export 24 or 48 bit?
                          ; Default: 48
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PNM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SUPPRESS_HEADER
                          ; setting this keyword will suppres
                          ; writing the PNM header for P5/P6
                          ; files, which actually will generate
                          ; a RAW data file, which cannot be loaded
                          ; with sview5.library again, but may be
                          ; used for different purposes
                          ; Default: (not set)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Printer.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - DENSITY=<density value for printing quality>
                          ; Amiga's printer device does allow seven
                          ; modes of printing density (1-7)
                          ; (not with TurboPrint)
                          ; default is: 3
                        - DISABLE_TURBOPRINT
                          ; If set, TurboPrint support is disabled.
                          ; default is: <not set>
                        - DISABLE_STUDIO
                          ; If set, Studio support is disabled.
                          ; default is: <not set>
                        - DISABLE_OS35_24BIT
                          ; If set, OS 3.5+ 24 Bit support is disabled.
                          ; default is: <not set>
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/QL.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - QL_MODE=<AUTO|QL4|QL8>
                          ; Determine QL mode from file extension
                          ; automatically, or use mode 4/8 explicitely?
                        - EXOTIC_FORMATS
                          ; Setting this keyword will enable exotic
                          ; formats support as described above;
                          ; not all formats may work in every version
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RAW.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - LUT8_FORMAT=<PLANAR|CHUNKY>
                          ; Write 8 bit as bitmap or as chunky buffer?
                          ; default: PLANAR
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RAW-CM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - RGB_BITS=<4|8>
                          ; Mask out lower 4 bit of LUT8 entries?
                          ; default: 8
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RAW-IMPORT.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ENDIAN=<BIG|LITTLE>
                          ; Endianess of 24/48 bit RGB data
                          ; (24: BGR->RGB, 48: RGB->RGB)
                          ; default: BIG
                        - FORMAT=<GRAY8|RGB24|RGBA32|ARGB32|
                                  RGB+A32|RGB48|RGBA64|ARGB64|
                                  RGB+A64|BAYER8>
                          ; Kind of RAW format to be imported
                          ; default: GRAY8
                        - LUT8_FORMAT=<CHUNKY|PLANAR>
                          ; Kind of LUT8 flavour to be imported
                          ; default: CHUNKY
                        - WIDTH=<value>
                          ; Pixel width of RAW data to be imported
                          ; default is: 1
                        - HEIGHT=<value>
                          ; Pixel height of RAW data to be imported
                          ; default is: 1
                        - LOADNAME=<filename>
                          ; File to load (suppress file requester)
                          ; use this if you write an ARexx script
                        - LOAD_CM=<ON|OFF>
                          ; GRAY8/LUT8: check for .cm file and load it?
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RAW-META.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - TEXT_FIELD=<Auth|Anno|Copy|Name|More1|More2|More3|More4>
                          ; Metadata text to extract (for "RAW-META (Text)")
                          ; default: Copy
                        - IPTC_TYPE=<RAW|APP13>
                          ; Include APP13 PS3 8BIM Header?
                          ; default: RAW
                        - EXIF_TYPE=<RAW|APP1>
                          ; Include APP1 EXIF Header?
                          ; default: APP1
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RAW-META-IMPORT.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling dcraw,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 65536
                        - FORMAT=<EXIF|IPTC|XMP0|XMP1|AUTH|ANNO|COPY|NAME>
                          ; Kind of RAW format to be imported
                          ; default: EXIF
                        - WIDTH=<value>
                          ; width of dummy graphics to be created for import
                          ; default: 1
                        - HEIGHT=<value>
                          ; height of dummy graphics to be created for import
                          ; default: 1
                        - DEPTH=<8|24|48>
                          ; width of dummy graphics to be created for import
                          ; default: 8
                        - LOADNAME=<filename>
                          ; File to load (suppress file requester)
                          ; use this if you write an ARexx script
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RGFX.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PACKMETHOD=<xxxx>
                          ; XPK packer to be used for writing
                          ; "RGFX xpk-compressed" ("ZIP" if none given)
                          ; Default: NUKE
                        - Z_COMPRESSION=<0..9>
                          ; allows changes in compression/speed.
                          ; 0 results in uncompressed data, 9 compresses
                          ; best, but increases decompression time.
                          ; Default: 6
                        - SAVE_CHUNKY
                          ; forces chunky data to be saved,
                          ; even if source graphics was planar
                          ; (e.g. when converting from IFF-ILBM)
                          ; May also result in smaller files.
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Scanner.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PUBSCREEN_NAME=<PubScreenName>
                          ; where the scanner drivers should open
                          ; their windows (if not set or not available,
                          ; the default Public Screen will be used).
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/SPP.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling SPP,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - SPP_PATH=<SPP command path plus name>
                          ; how SPP is to be called
                          ; e.g. SPP_PATH=Work:SPP/SPP-030-881
                          ; default is: SPP
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
                        - LOSSY_FACTOR
                          ; 0..12, where 0 means non-lossy
                          ; default is: 0
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/SVG.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PACKMETHOD=<xxxx>
                          ; if this one is specified, it is tried to
                          ; pack the resulting file with the specified
                          ; XPK-Packer. If this fails, the file keeps
                          ; unpacked.
                        - Z_COMPRESSION=<0..9>
                          ; allows changes in compression/speed.
                          ; 0 results in uncompressed data, 9 compresses
                          ; best, but increases decompression time.
                          ; Default: 6
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/SVG-W3C.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling svg2png
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - SVG2PNG_PATH=<svg2png command path plus name>
                          ; how SVG2PNG is to be called
                          ; e.g. SVG2PNG_PATH=Work:SVGTools/svg2png
                          ; default is: svg2png (FOR LOADING)
                        - POTRACE_PATH=<potrace command path plus name>
                          ; how POTRACE is to be called
                          ; e.g. POTRACE_PATH=Work:potrace-1.7/bin/potrace.elf
                          ; default is: potrace
                        - WIDTH=<value>
                          ; stretch to given width
                          ; default is: - (do not stretch)
                        - HEIGHT=<value>
                          ; stretch to given width
                          ; default is: - (do not stretch)
                        - POTRACE_COLOR=<hex value>
                          ; Line color for potrace (default: black)
                          ; default is: (black)
                        - POTRACE_FILLCOLOR=<hex value>
                          ; Fill color for potrace (default: transparent)
                          ; default is: (transparent)
                        - POTRACE_OPAQUE=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Make white shapes opaque with potrace?
                          ; default is: OFF
                        - POTRACE_INVERT=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Invert Bitmap with potrace?
                          ; default is: OFF
                        - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/TIFF.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PAGENUMBER=<0..n>
                          ; number of image to be displayed
                          ; (e.g. for TIFFs with image directories
                          ;  or multi-page FAX documents)
                        - READ_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Parse EXIF data during reading?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - WRITE_EXIF=<ON|OFF>
                          ; DESCRIPTION=Write EXIF data (specific tags, where supported)?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - READ_IPTC=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Parse IPTC data during reading?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - IS_EXIF=<TRUE|FALSE>
                          ; Is this a EXIF TIFF from inside raw JPEG APP1?
                          ; (set PAGENUMBER=1 for loading thumbnail)
                          ; default is: FALSE
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Unpack.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STATUS=<ENABLED|DISABLED>
                          ; allows to disable this module - for example
                          ; to be able to use an other, program-specific
                          ; import-module for the same file format
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/UtahRLE.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - NO_ROTATE
                          ; do not rotate images on load/save
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/YUVN.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - READ_ALPHA=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Read alpha channel (DATA/DATO)?
                          ; default is: ON
                        - WRITE_ALPHA=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Write alpha channel (DATO)?
                          ; default is: ON
  ============================================================================
  SVDRIVERS
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AGA.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - 24BITOPERATOR=<OperatorName>
                          ; (case-sensitive, ".sv5operator" may be added)
                          ; e.g. "24BITOPERATOR=24BitToHAM.sv5operator"
                          ; or   "24BITOPERATOR=ExtractGrayScales"
                          ; specifies, which operation should be performed
                          ; on 24 bit graphics _before_ displaying them
                          ; (if not specified, "best guess" colors will
                          ;  be used, which is really slow)
                        - BITMAPCOPY=<DIRECT|RTG>
                          ; "BITMAPCOPY=RTG" prevents AGA.sv5driver from
                          ; directly copying into Bitmaps, which will
                          ; result in a usage of more memory, but keeps it
                          ; working.
                          ; Default is "BITMAPCOPY=DIRECT".
                        - SCREENINFRONT
                          ; Put Screen to front _before_ the graphics
                          ; has been displayed (useful with GfxCards)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ECS.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - 24BITOPERATOR=<OperatorName>
                          ; (case-sensitive, ".sv5operator" may be added)
                          ; e.g. "24BITOPERATOR=24BitToHAM.sv5operator"
                          ; or   "24BITOPERATOR=ExtractGrayScales"
                          ; specifies, which operation should be performed
                          ; on 24 bit graphics _before_ displaying them
                          ; (if not specified displaying will fail)
                        - 8BITOPERATOR=<OperatorName>
                          ; (case-sensitive, ".sv5operator" may be added)
                          ; e.g. "8BITOPERATOR=ExtractGrayScales"
                          ; specifies, which operation should be performed
                          ; on non-ECS graphics (more than 16 Colors in
                          ; HighRes, more than 32 Colors in LowRes, HAM8)
                          ; (if not specified, will be tried to display)
                        - BITMAPCOPY=<DIRECT|RTG>
                          ; "BITMAPCOPY=RTG" prevents ECS.sv5driver from
                          ; directly copying into Bitmaps, which will
                          ; result in a usage of more memory, but keeps it
                          ; working.
                          ; Default is "BITMAPCOPY=DIRECT".
                        - SCREENINFRONT
                          ; Put Screen to front _before_ the graphics
                          ; has been displayed (useful with GfxCards)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/CgxOverlay.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PUBSCREEN_NAME=<PubScreenName>
                          ; where the window driver should open
                          ; its windows (if not set or not available,
                          ; the default Public Screen will be used).
                        - REFRESHMODE=<SMART|SIMPLE>
                          ; window refresh mode
                          ; default: SMART
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/CyberGraphics.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - EMUSCREENDEPTH=<16|24>
                          ; beginning depth for opening CyberGraphics Screens
                          ; Default is 16 Bit (which will also be tried
                          ; when opening of a 24 bit Screen fails)
                          ; This does not concern colordepths < 16 Bit,
                          ; except HAM6/8.
                        - SMALLSCREENS
                          ; unless this keyword is specified, it is not
                          ; tried to open screens smaller than 320x240
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Picasso96.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SMALLSCREENS
                          ; unless this keyword is specified, it is not
                          ; tried to open screens smaller than 320x240
                        - EMUSCREENDEPTH=<16|24>
                          ; beginning depth for opening Picasso96 Screens
                          ; Default is 24 bit (if opening fails, it is
                          ; also tried to open a 16 Bit Screen, then)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Window.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - 24BITOPERATOR=<OperatorName>
                          ; (case-sensitive, ".sv5operator" may be added)
                          ; e.g. "24BITOPERATOR=Dither24Bit.sv5operator"
                          ; or   "24BITOPERATOR=ExtractGrayScales"
                          ; specifies, which operation should be performed
                          ; on 24 bit graphics _before_ displaying them
                          ; on a screen with a colordepth <= 8
                          ; (if not specified, "best guess" colors will
                          ;  be used, which is really slow). Note, that
                          ; HAM is not allowed (thus don't specify the
                          ; 24BitToHAM operator).
                        - SCROLLSPEED=<Pixels>
                          ; determines, how many pixel should
                          ; be scrolled in any direction when
                          ; being in scroll mode and a cursor key
                          ; is pressed
                          ; Default: 10 (medium slow)
                        - PUBSCREEN_NAME=<PubScreenName>
                          ; where the window driver should open
                          ; its windows (if not set or not available,
                          ; the default Public Screen will be used).
                        - SCROLLMODE=<AUTO|NEVER|ALWAYS>
                          ; - 'ALWAYS' activates scroll mode even for
                          ; non-oversized graphics; this will block
                          ; the input of the calling program as
                          ; long as no key or mouse button has been
                          ; pressed inside the display window - but
                          ; will avoid window-refresh problems.
                          ; - 'NEVER' is to avoid the blocking of
                          ; input handling that is caused by the
                          ; scrolling handler
                          ; Default: AUTO
                        - TRUECOLOR8
                          ; if the Pubscreen is a 24 bit screen but
                          ; the graphics to be displayed is 'only'
                          ; 8 bit or HAM6/8, usually remapping is
                          ; done nevertheless. This option instead
                          ; allows to call "AnyTo24Bit" first,
                          ; thus giving better display quality
                          ; on 24 bit screens. This is memory
                          ; intensive, because for scrolling we
                          ; need another complete 24 bit buffer.
                          ; (requires AnyTo24Bit.sv5operator)
                        - PEN_PRECISION=<IMAGE|EXACT>
                          ; you should not change this
                          ; default: IMAGE
                        - REFRESHMODE=<SMART|SIMPLE>
                          ; window refresh mode
                          ; default: SMART
  ============================================================================
  SVOPERATORS
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/24BitToHAM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - DITHERMODE=< HAM6_QUICK|HAM6_WELL
                                      |HAM8_QUICK|HAM8_WELL>
                          ; specifies the HAM-Mode to be used and
                          ; the resulting speed/quality
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AddAlpha.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ALPHA_VALUE=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBBAA>
                          ; RGB pixel value and Alpha Value in Hex
                          ; FF == opaque, 00 == transparent
                          ; default: 0x000000FF
                        - ALPHA_MODE=<SOURCE|ALL|VALUE>
                          : Use 8 bit source? Or fixed value? If fixed:
                          ; Set Alpha Value for all pixels or only
                          ; those matching the specified RGB value?
                          ; default: ALL
                        - ALPHA_SOURCE=<Path to graphics file>
                          ; This is the source graphics from ALPHA_MODE;
                          ; it must be 8 bit, to be used as alpha channel
                          ; in form of its grayscale shape
                        - SCALE_SOURCEGFX=<ON|OFF>
                          ; Scale Alpha Source if wrong size? Otherwise error!
                          ; default: ON
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AddTransColor.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - COLOR_NUM=<Palette Entry Num>
                          ; Which color of the palette should be transparent?
                          ; Note: only in TRANS_MODE=NUM
                          ; default: 0
                        - COLOR_VALUE=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBB00>
                          ; Which RGB color in the palette should be
                          ; transparent?
                          ; If you do not know the palette entry num,
                          ; the first matching entry will be made transparent.
                          ; Use "OptimizePalette" first in case you have
                          ; duplicate entries.
                          ; Note: only in TRANS_MODE=VALUE
                          ; default: 0x00000000
                        - TRANS_MODE=<NUM|VALUE>
                          ; Operare in which mode? See above!
                          ; default: NUM
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/AlphaBlend.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ALPHA_MODE=<SRCGFX_ALPHA|BLENDGFX_ALPHA>
                          ; Use source/blendgfx graphics alpha channel?
                          ; default: SRCGFX_ALPHA
                        - BLEND_GRAPHICS=<Path to graphics file>
                          ; This is the blend graphics from ALPHA_MODE;
                          ; if it has no Alpha Channel, just specify
                          ; SRC_ALPHA instead. Note: must be 24 bit
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/CallPNM.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - STACKSIZE=<value>
                          ; stacksize to be used for calling PNM program,
                          ; increasing may help on crashes
                          ; default is: 32768
                        - USE_PAM_FOR_ALPHA
                          ; setting this keyword will suppress
                          ; enforce usage of PNM PAM (P7) format
                          ; if the input graphics has an alpha
                          ; channel attached; note, that older NetPBM
                          ; versions cannot handle PAM format; not
                          ; setting this options strips the alpha
                          ; channel by usage of the backward-compatible
                          ; PNM PPM (P6) format which lacks alpha support
                          ; Default: (not set)
                        - NETPBM_PATH=<netpbm command path>
                          ; folder from where NetPBM is to be called
                          ; e.g. NETPBM_PATH=Work:NetPBM/
                          ; COMPATIBILITY ISSUE: if left empty, it
                          ; is assumed that the path is part of the
                          ; PNMCOMMAND setting
                          ; default is: <empty>
                        - COMMAND_FILE=<command file name>
                          ; separate file for command & options definition,
                          ; overriding global PNMCOMMAND/PNMOPTIONS
                          ; default: (not set)
                        - PNMCOMMAND=<PBM command path and name>
                          ; PNM command to be called
                          ; e.g. PNMCOMMAND=Work:NetPBM/pnm/pnmscale
                        - PNMOPTIONS=<Options>
                          ; Options for PNM command to be called
                          ; e.g. PNMOPTIONS=-xscale 2.0 -yscale 2.0
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ChangePalette.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PALETTE_SOURCE=<Source graphics for palette>
                          ; filename of colormapped graphics that holds
                          ; the new palette to be used
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Crop.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SV_AREA=<left,top,width,height>
                          ; Area to crop
                        - CROP_LEFTEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from x position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source width)
                        - CROP_TOPEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from y position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source height)
                        - CROP_WIDTH=<Value>
                          ; crop how many x pixels from leftedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
                        - CROP_HEIGHT=<Value>
                          ; crop how many y pixels from topedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Cut.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SV_AREA=<left,top,width,height>
                          ; Area to cut
                        - BACKPEN=<0..255>
                          ; 8 Bit RGB pen index
                        - BACKCOLOR=<0x000000>
                          ; 24 Bit RRGGBB value
                        - CUT_LEFTEDGE=<Value>
                          ; cut at x position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source width)
                        - CUT_TOPEDGE=<Value>
                          ; cut at y position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source height)
                        - CUT_WIDTH=<Value>
                          ; cut how many x pixels from leftedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
                        - CUT_HEIGHT=<Value>
                          ; cut how many y pixels from topedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/CutInverse.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SV_AREA=<left,top,width,height>
                          ; Area to cut inverse
                        - BACKPEN=<0..255>
                          ; 8 Bit RGB pen index
                        - BACKCOLOR=<0x000000>
                          ; 24 Bit RRGGBB value
                        - CUT_LEFTEDGE=<Value>
                          ; cut at x position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source width)
                        - CUT_TOPEDGE=<Value>
                          ; cut at y position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source height)
                        - CUT_WIDTH=<Value>
                          ; cut how many x pixels from leftedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
                        - CUT_HEIGHT=<Value>
                          ; cut how many y pixels from topedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Dither24Bit.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - COLORDEPTH=<1..8>
                          ; specifies the colordepth of the dithering
                          ; output (1->2 Colors .. 8->256 Colors)
                        - DITHERMODE=<BESTPEN|DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG
                                      |ORDERED|BURKES>
                          ; whether to just select the best pen or
                          ; do Floyd-Steinberg pixel error adjustment
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/DitherFix24.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - COLORDEPTH=<1..8>
                          ; specifies the colordepth of the dithering
                          ; output (1->2 Colors .. 8->256 Colors)
                        - DITHERMODE=<BESTPEN|DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG>
                          ; whether to just select the best pen or
                          ; do Floyd-Steinberg pixel error adjustment

                        - [ plus a few more undocumented options ]
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ExtractGrayScales.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - COLORDEPTH=<1..8>
                          ; specifies the colordepth of the grayscaled
                          ; output (1->2 Colors .. 8->256 Colors)
                        - QUICK
                          ; uses >>2, >>1, >>3 (*0.25, *0.5, *0.125)
                          ; instead of *0.3, *0.59, *0.11
                        - SORTED8BIT=<NONE|ASCENDING|DESCENDING>
                          ; specifies the sort order for the
                          ; destination grayscale color map
                          ; default: ASCENDING
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/FixAlphaBlend.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ALPHA_VALUE=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBBAA>
                          ; RGB pixel value and Alpha Value in Hex
                          ; FF == opaque, 00 == transparent
                          ; Source alpha ignored, if any!
                          ; default: 0x000000FF
                        - ALPHA_PIXEL24=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBB>
                          ; RGB pixel value, only
                          ; default: 0x000000
                        - ALPHA_VALUE8=<0..255>
                          ; Alpha value, only
                          ; default: 255
                        - USE_SOURCEALPHA
                          ; Use Source Alpha Channel. Specified value ignored!
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/FlipNibbles.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - FLIPMODE=<SWAP|MINUS_LOW|MINUS_HIGH|SHIFT_LOW|SHIFT_HIGH>
                          ; Operating mode (see documentation)
                          ; default: SWAP
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/HilbertDither256.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - BACKGROUND=<BLACK|WHITE>
                          ; defines, which of the two colors will act
                          ; as background color. Useful e.g. for printing.
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Histogram.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - HISTROGRAM_PATH=<external text file>
                          ; Store a textual histogram? Where?
                          ; default is: <N/A>
                        - MODE=<COLOR|BRIGHTNESS>
                          ; What to count and show in histogram?
                          ; default: BRIGHTNESS
                        - WIDTH=<value>
                          ; Brightness mode: Width of histogram page (rotated Y-Axis)
                          ; default: 100
                        - BACKCOLOR_VALUE=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBB>
                          ; Brightness mode: Background color VALUE in 0xRRGGBB format
                          ; default: 0x000000
                        - FORECOLOR_VALUE=<Hex Value 0xRRGGBB>
                          ; Brightness mode: Foreground color VALUE in 0xRRGGBB format
                          ; default: 0xFFFFFF
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/InvertAlpha.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - NO_ALPHA=<IGNORE|ERROR|OPAQUE|TRANSPARENT>
                          ; If the source graphics has no alpha channel
                          ; and nothing can be inverted, do what?
                          ; IGNORE:      just copy it and return 24 bit
                          ; ERROR:       throw an error and return nothing
                          ; OPAQUE:      add alpha, but leave it opaque,
                          ;              which is like ignore but with alpha
                          ; TRANSPARENT: add alpha, but invert it,
                          ;              which is the opposite of ignore
                          ; default:     IGNORE
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Move.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - SV_AREA=<left,top,width,height>
                          ; Area to move
                        - BACKPEN=<0..255>
                          ; 8 Bit RGB pen index for empty part
                        - BACKCOLOR=<0x000000>
                          ; 24 Bit RRGGBB value for empty part
                        - DELTA_X=<Value>
                          ; Offset to shift in X direction (+/-)
                        - DELTA_Y=<Value>
                          ; Offset to shift in Y direction (+/-)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PagePrint.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - NAMELIST=<filename>
                          ; specifies the image file names,
                          ; which should become part of the thumbail
                          ; overview (one file name per line)
                        - TEXTNUMLINES=<lines>
                          ; how many lines of text should be
                          ; printed below each thumbnail?

                        - [ plus a few more undocumented options ]
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/PaletteDither.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - COLORDEPTH=<1..8>
                          ; specifies the colordepth of the final,
                          ; dithered graphics (1..8 for 2..256 colors)
                          ; default: 8
                        - DITHERMODE=<BESTPEN|DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG>
                          ; whether to just select the best pen or
                          ; do Floyd-Steinberg pixel error adjustment
                          ; default: DITHER_FLOYD-STEINBERG
                        - PALETTEDEPTH=<1..8>
                          ; number of colors (depth) to be taken from the
                          ; fixed palette - the possible rest will be
                          ; generated (if specifying more palette colors
                          ; than available, all available will be taken)
                          ; default: 8
                        - PALETTEFILE=<palette graphics filename>
                          ; any 2..256 color graphics file, of which
                          ; sview5.library is able to extract a
                          ; palette from (for example an IFF-ILBM file,
                          ; but including a BMHD and - maybe empty - BODY).
                          ; Allows to take one graphics as sample for
                          ; the others (concerning the palette).
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Resize.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - NEW_WIDTH=<width>
                          ; new width
                        - NEW_HEIGHT=<height>
                          ; new height
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Rotate.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - DEGREES=<90|180|270>
                          ; rotate by how many degrees (reverse clockwise) ?
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/RotateFree.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ROTATE_ANGLE=<0..360>
                          ; rotate by how many degrees (reverse clockwise) ?
                        - METHOD=<MIDDLE|GIVENPOINT>
                          ; default is rotation about the middle
                        - X_COORD=<Value>
                          ; if METHOD=GIVENPOINT we need (X/Y)
                          ; Default is (0/0)
                        - Y_COORD=<Value>
                          ; if METHOD=GIVENPOINT we need (X/Y)
                          ; Default is (0/0)
                        - KEEPSIZE
                          ; if this keyword is set, it is NOT tried to
                          ; readjust the image size and to center the
                          ; image, so that parts, which would be out of
                          ; range won't be cut off (which works best
                          ; with (X/Y) pairs in the left, upper quarter)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/Scale50.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - METHOD=<HALF|DOUBLE>
                          ; scale to which size ?
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/ScaleDDA.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - ZOOM_FACTOR=<factor>
                          ; greater than 1.0 (increase size)
                          ; smaller than 1.0 (decrease size)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/SQBentley.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands :   ; The following controlpads allow you to apply
                          ; this operator to a rectangular region of the
                          ; image.
                        - REGION=<ENTIREIMAGE|RECTANGULAR>
                          ; area of image to work on
                        - LEFTEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from x position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source width)
                        - TOPEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from y position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source height)
                        - WIDTH=<Value>
                          ; crop how many x pixels from leftedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
                        - HEIGHT=<Value>
                          ; crop how many y pixels from topedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ControlPad-Name     : "ENV:SView5-Library/SQBlur.controlpad"
  ControlPad-Commands : - PERCENTAGE=<1..100>
                          ; This the percentage of Blur to be applied.
                          ;
                          ; The following controlpads allow you to apply
                          ; this operator to a rectangular region of the
                          ; image.
                        - REGION=<ENTIREIMAGE|RECTANGULAR>
                          ; area of image to work on
                        - LEFTEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from x position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source width)
                        - TOPEDGE=<Value>
                          ; crop from y position
                          ; (will be adjusted, if >= source height)
                        - WIDTH=<Value>
                          ; crop how many x pixels from leftedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
                        - HEIGHT=<Value>
                          ; crop how many y pixels from topedge
                          ; (will be adjusted, if too large)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
